Commentary: Sharma starts with an outswinger outside the off stump line, Crawley watches it carefully and then lets it go to the keeper. Good carry first up to Pant.

NOT OUT! India lose a review as the ball would have missed the stumps. Ishant Sharma was confident but the review went in vain. Sharma bowls a good length ball on middle, Crawley looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Ishant Sharma puts up a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Ishant tells his skipper that there is absolutely no bat on it and Kohli opts for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is no bat. What about Ball Tracker? It shows that it is missing the stumps. India lose a review.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.
Ishant bowls an inswinger around off, Crawley prods forward and then defends it to cover.
On a length outside off, Crawley has no problems in leaving it alone.
That one hit the gloves! Good length ball on off, angling in, Zak looks to defend but the ball comes in and hits him on the gloves. Excellent first over from Ishant Sharma.
Sibley and England are off the mark! Good length ball on off, Sibley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes through the gully region for a couple of runs.
There is good carry on this wicket! Siraj dishes a good length ball outside off, it bounces a little more but Sibley watches it go through to the keeper.

BEATEN! Well bowled, Siraj! Superb stuff from Siraj! Good length ball around off, it tails away after pitching. Sibley prods forward to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and it goes to the keeper.

FOUR LEG BYES! Ishant Sharma will not get there! Good length ball on the pads, Sibley looks to flick but it brushes his pads and goes to fine leg. Ishant Sharma runs across but is way too far to stop it and the ball goes into the fence.
Fullish ball on off, Sibley takes a stride forward and defends it to the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley is solid in defense.
Excllent carry to the keeper once again! Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend at first but then gets his bat away at the last moment. It goes at a good height to Pant.
PLAY AND A MISS! Loose shot from Crawley! There was no need to play at this one! Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
Crawley is off the mark with a couple of runs! Fullish ball on off, Crawley drives it through the mid off region. Sharma dives to stop but gets only fingertips on it. A couple taken.
Fullish ball on off, Crawley nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley watches it carefully this time and then leaves it alone.
A single to end the over! Ishant bowls an indipper on middle, Zak works it to square leg and crosses over for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to Pant behind the stumps.
Good length ball on off, Crawley takes a stride forward and then looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fullish ball on off, Crawley defends it to cover off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Crawley taps it to the slip cordon and says no for the single.
Fullish ball outside off, Crawley drives but finds the fielder at point.
EDGY! False shot induced but safe! Siraj bowls a full ball outside off, Crawley looks to drive but gets an inside edge and it goes to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, Zak goes on his back foot and then blocks it to the off side.
BEATEN! Superb piece of bowling from Ishant Sharma! This one held its line. Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend but it beats the outside edge and goes to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Zak shoulders arms to it.
Just past the off stump! Sharma has his hands over his head! This was very close! Good length ball outside off, it comes in sharply. Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Crawley defends it to the point region.
Axar starts with a floated ball on middle, Sibley defends it to short leg.

OUT! TIMBER! There he goes! Axar Patel comes into the attack and gets a breakthrough. It is once again the straighter delivery which has done the trick. England lose a wicket early yet again. Axar bowls a loopy ball on off, Sibley prods forward to defend and looks to play for the turn but it does not spin and goes straight on. It takes the inside edge of Sibley's bat and goes onto hit the top of leg stump. Axar Patel takes a wicket in his first over again. He has had a terrific start to his Test career.
Almost another one! Quicker ball on middle, Bairstow goes back in his crease and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the back pad.
Full ball outside off, Bairstow drives it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Bairstow looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards short leg.
Loopy ball on middle, Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball around odd, angling in. Crawley hops and looks to defend but it hits his gloves and goes to the leg side. A single taken.
Full ball outside off, Bairstow lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball outside off, Bairstow watches it go to the keeper.
That flew to Rishabh Pant! Very full ball outside off, Bairstow looks to dig it out but fails. That went quickly to Pant but he does well to collect it.
Full ball down the leg side, Bairstow looks to flick but misses.
A midl appeal for LBW! Probably going down leg. Good length ball on middle and leg, Bairstow looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but it is turned down.
FOUR! Wonderful shot by Crawley! First boundary off the bat in this innings! Tossed up on off, Crawley uses his feet and then drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Loopy ball on middle, Crawley defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Zak dances down the track and then defends it to short cover.
Flighted ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT AT MID OFF! He was trying to unsettle the bowler but the execution was poor. Crawley was trying to be positive but overdid his footwork on this occasion. Axar Patel continues to motor along. 20 wickets already in the series and this match has only started. Tossed up on off, Crawley uses his feet and then looks to go over mid off but it lobs off the lower part of the bat and goes straight up in the air. Siraj settles himself under it and mid off and takes the simplest of catches. England in trouble yet again.
Shorter on off, Root defends it to cover.
Short ball around off, Bairstow sways away from it.
Full ball outside the off stump line, Bairstow shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Bairstow is off the mark! This will give Bairstow a lot of relief. He was out for a pair in the last Test match. Good length ball outside off, Bairstow tentatively pushes at it and it goes through gully for a boundary.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Ishant! Good length ball outside off, Bairstow looks to defend but beats the outside edge.
Good length ball on off, Bairstow defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on the pads, Jonny flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Bairstow works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, Bairstow prods forward to defend.
Full on off, Jonny pushes it to cover.
Quicker on middle, JB pushes it to mid off and takes a quick single.
Just past short leg! Root is off the mark! Floated ball on middle, Root looks to defend but it takes the inner half of the bat and it goes past short leg for a single.
Full on middle, Jonny plays it back to the bowler.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good carry to the keeper. Back of a length ball around off, Root does not expect it to bounce so much and looks to defend but misses as it goes to the keeper.
Fullish ball outside off, Root leaves it alone.
BEATEN! This is excellent bowling from Siraj! On a length outside off, Root looks to defend but it whizzes past the outside edge and it goes to the keeper.
Fullish ball on off, Root gets behind the line of the ball and then solidly pushes it to cover.
Siraj bowls an inswinger on middle, Root looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad. Good over so far from Siraj.
FOUR! Plays it fine! Siraj digs one short and around middle, Root looks to pull but it goes off the top edge and to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Loopy ball on the pads, JB nudges it to mid-wicket.

EDGED AND FOUR! Not too far from Ajinkya Rahane at first slip! Streaky boundary. Flatter ball outside off, Bairstow looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and it flies past first slip for a boundary.
Full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Jonny uses his feet and then defends it back to the bowler.
On off, Bairstow prods forward and then defends it back to Axar.
Full on middle, Jonny takes a stride forward and defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! Root knows that he is stone-dead there as he turns to go back to the pavilion. Siraj strikes and it is of the big fish, Joe Root. Siraj bowls a good length ball on off, it angles in after pitching. Root is stuck in the crease as he looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. India appeal and up goes the finger. Root consults his partner whether to take the review but he knows that he is a goner and walks back without taking the review. Siraj troubled Root in the previous over and the English skipper was not looking confident against him. Good decision not to review as the Ball Tracker shows all reds.
EDGY! Good length ball outside off, Stokes looks to leave it alone but is late as the ball takes the outside edge and it goes to the second slip fielder.
Fullish ball outside off, Stokes lets it through to the keeper.
On a length on middle and leg, Ben pushes it back to the bowler.
Stokes is off the mark in an edgy manner! Good length ball on middle and leg, Stokes looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes through the point region. A couple taken.
Bouncer outside off, Stokes sways away from it.
Flatter ball on off, Bairstow looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes to point.
On middle, Bairstow works it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on middle, Jonny defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, pushed back to Axar.
Outside off, left alone.
Flatter ball outside off, Bairstow looks to cut but misses.
NO BALL! Good length ball outside off, Stokes lets it go. No Ball signalled by the third umpire.
FOUR! Edgy but Stokes won't mind! Good length ball around off, Stokes looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes past Sharma at second slip for a boundary.
On off, tapped to gully.
On a length on middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Not middled but has enough to fetch a boundary. Siraj bowls a short one around off, Stokes looks to pull but it takes the toe end of the bat and it goes through mid-wicket for a boundary.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on off, Stokes looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes through gully for a boundary. Some words exchanged by the bowler and Stokes.
Fullish ball on off, Ben defends it to cover.
Flatter ball on the pads, Bairstow nudges it to short fine leg where the fielder makes a good stop.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Bairstow uses his feet and then flicks it to short fine leg for a dot.
Shorter on the pads, tucked to the leg side.
FOUR! Cut and cut away nicely by Bairstow! This will do a lot of good to his confidence. Flatter ball on off, Bairstow goes back in his crease and then punches it to deep cover for a boundary.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Jonny defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish ball on off, Stokes takes a few steps forward and then defends it to point.
Good length ball on off, BS pushes it to the point region.
Outside off, left alone.
Full ball on the pads, Stokes flicks it wide of mid on for a single. 50 up for England.
Full on off, Jonny bunts it down to mid off.
On off, defended out.
Loopy ball on off, Stokes lunges forward and then blocks it out.
EDGY! Stokes is living dangerously! Flighted ball on middle, Stokes looks to sweep but it takes the top edge and goes over the keeper for a single.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Quicker ball on middle, Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor ball from Axar Patel and Bairstow punishes him! Shorter and way outside off, Bairstow cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Back of a length ball down the leg side, Stokes leaves it alone.
On middle, punched back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes tucks it to fine leg for a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! Width offered by Ishant and a boundary conceded! Back of a length ball outside off, Bairstow looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and it flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Good length ball on the pads, Jonny looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. It goes to fine leg for a leg bye.
Outside off, left alone by Ben.
Ashwin starts with a floated ball on middle, Jonny flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Full on middle, Jonny flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter on off, Ben goes back in his crease and then defends it to cover.
SIX! There he goes! Stokes does not want Ashwin to settle! Loopy ball on off, Stokes uses his feet and then lifts it over long off for a maximum. First one in the game.
Darted on off, Stokes defends it to cover.
FOUR! Again width offered and these are easy pickkings for Bairstow! Shorter and outside off, Bairstow cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Good length on middle and leg, Bairstow looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. Much better from Ishant.
Full ball outside off, Bairstow looks to drive but gets a bottom edge which goes back to the keeper who collects it on the bounce.
Full ball outside off, Jonny shoulders arms to it.
On a length on off, Jonny defends it to cover.
Good length ball outside of,f Bairstow lunges forward and looks to leave it alone but gets hit on the back pad. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
Tossed up on off, Stokes defends it to cover.
Flatter ball on off, tapped to the first slip fielder.
Quicker on off, Stokes punches it back to Ashwin. No run.
Full and on middle, Stokes is solid in defense.
Full on off, bunted to cover.
Flatter on middle, Stokes defends it to silly point.

NOT OUT! Bairstow is in! No one looked that confident and Bairstow has made it way back in. The last thing that England would have needed was a run out. Flighted ball on middle, Bairstow flicks it to square leg and takes off for a single but Stokes is not interested and sends him back. Pujara collects the ball and throws it to Pant who whips the bails off. The third umpire is called for but the replays show that Bairstow is in.
On the pads, nudged to the leg side.
Flatter on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Jonny defends it out.
Tossed up on middle, JB solidly pushes it back to Axar.
Full on middle, Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, blocked back to Ashwin.
Flighted ball on middle, Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, Stokes nudges it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Stokes defends it to the off side.
Outside off, left alone by Stokes.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled by Ashwin! Tossed up outside off, Stokes lunges forward and looks to cream the drive through the covers but fails to get any bat on it. Good ball to end the over.
Flatter on the pads, Bairstow works it wide of mid on for a single.
Flighted ball on the pads, Stokes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Bairstow pushes it to cover.
Flighted ball outside off, Bairstow lets this go to the keeper.
Loopy ball on the pads, Bairstow nudges it to the leg side for a single.
Full on middle, worked to mid on. LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Ashwin starts with a floated ball outside off, Stokes has no problems in leaving it alone.
Loopy ball on off, Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on off, Ben defends it off the back foot.
First run of the session! Full ball outside off, Stokes drives it to deep cover.
Down the leg side, Bairstow lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on middle, Bairstow punches it back to the bowler. A run from the first over after Lunch.
Full on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off from the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Ben lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Ben looks to work it on the leg side but it takes the leading edge and it goes to the off side.
Nicely punched away! Good length ball outside off, Stokes punches it off the back foot and picks up a couple before Pujara cuts it off.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes plays it to mid off.
Full on the pads, Stokes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Stokes pushes it to silly point.
Flat on middle, Stokes works it down to mid on.
On off, pushed to point.
Floated on off, Stokes lunges forward and then plays it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Stokes is solid in defense.

NOT OUT! Impact is outside off and the Indians have lost another review. Rishabh Pant was not convinced but Kohli went with his bowler.  Loopy ball on off, Stokes looks to defend but it seems to have hit the pad first and then the bat. Ashwin appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Ashwin, Pant and Kohli are involved in an animated discussion and Kohli takes the review. The replays show that there is pad first. The Ball Tracker rolls on and it shows that the impact is outside off.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the stumps and Bairstow has to go! He is not impressed as he walks off in anger. Brilliant delivery from Siraj and he gets rewarded for his effort. Good length ball around off, it angles in sharply after pitching. Bairstow looks to defend but he seems to have missed it, hits the pads and goes to the keeper. Pant catches it. Indians appeal and up goes the finger. Bairstow takes the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is no bat on it while the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on impact. Bairstow was looking good but he has to go.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball on off, Pope defends it to cover.
Fullish ball on off, Pope pushes it to point.
Good length ball down the leg side, Pope looks to flick but misses.
Fullish ball on off, Pope strides forward and then blocks it to the off side.
Full on middle, Stokes plays it back to Ashwin.
Flatter ball on off, Ben pushes it to cover.
Flatter on middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Full on off, Stokes pushes it to cover.
Flighted ball outside off, Stokes plays it to point off the front foot.
Loopy ball on off, defended to the off side.
A couple now! Full ball outside off, Pope drives it through the cover region for a couple.
Good length ball on middle, Pope pushes it to mid on.
BYE! That was quick from Siraj! Bouncer around middle, Pope does well to duck under it. Pant hops but fails to collect and the batters collect a bye.
Good length ball on off, Stokes pushes it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, blocked to the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes nudges it to mid on for a single.
Floated ball outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Flighted ball on middle, Stokes defends it to cover.
FOUR! This is a wonderful shot by Stokes! Flighted ball on middle and leg, Stokes uses his feet and then flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, defended to point.
Flatter ball on middle, Stokes defends it to mid on.
Loopy ball on off, Stokes lunges forward and then blocks it to cover.
Full on off, Pope looks to drive but gets an inside edge towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Ollie works it wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ben solidly pushes it back to Siraj.
Full ball down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on off, Stokes blocks it off the back foot.
Floated ball on off, Pope lunges forward and then defends it to cover.
Loopy ball on the pads, Ollie works it to square leg for a single.
Full on off, Stokes defends it to cover.
Flatter ball outside off, Stokes plays it to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Stokes lunges forward and then blocks it out.
Flatter ball on off, Ben pushes it to point. Just 1 run from the over.
God shot but for nothing! Fullish ball outside off, Pope drives but finds the fielder at cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball outside off, Pope drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Good length ball on off, OP defends it to cover.
Outside off, pushed to mid off.
Well bowled by Siraj! Pope wa surprised by that! Short ball around off, Pope looked to sway away from it but fails to get away in time as the ball takes the inside edge onto the pads.

NOT OUT! It has bounced! Very full ball on middle, Stokes looks to flick but it seems to have gone on the bounce to the short leg fielder. Indians appeal and the two on-field umpires converge. They take it upstairs. The replays show that it has bounced in front.
On off, defended out.
Flatter ball down the leg side, Stokes lets it go. Pant fails to collect and a bye is collected.
On off, defended out.
That spun a lot! Flighted ball outside off, Pope withdrew his bat away at the last moment and lets it go.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! No need to run for these! Brilliant shot from Stokes! Full ball on middle, Stokes drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it to cover.
On middle, punched back to Siraj.
Short ball around leg, Stokes ducks under it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Siraj digs one short and outside off, Stokes looks to cut but misses it altogether.
Good length ball on off, Stokes efends it out.
Floated on off, Pope gets on his front foot and defends it to the off side.
Pope comes down the track and takes it as a low full toss. Pope then milks it to long off for one.
Short on off, Stokes knocks it through mid on with the spin for one.
Short on off, Pope keeps it out.
Axar gives this one a lot of air on off. Pope defends it to point.
Flighted on the stumps, Pope blocks it.
BEATEN! Beautiful start from Sundar! Floated ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but misses.
Floated outside off, punched to point.
Outside off, left alone.
Flighted ball on off, Stokes lunges forward and then blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Just wide of the first slip fielder! Good start from Sundar here! Loopy ball outside off, Stokes looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and it goes just wide of first slip for a couple.
Flighted ball outside off, Pope defends it to cover.
On middle, Pope defends it from the front foot.
Full on middle, Pope uses his feet and then plays it back to Patel.
Flatter ball on off, Pope defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Good shot from Pope! Brings up England's 100 as well! Flatter ball outside off, Pope cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Flighted ball on middle, Pope lunges forward and then blocks it to the off side.
Flighted ball outside off, Stokes lets it go to Pant.
Full on off, Ben defends it to point.
BEATEN! Lovely stuff from Sundar! Flatter and around off, Stokes looks to defend off the back foot but fails to get any bat on it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Sundar tosses this one up outside off, inviting Stokes to go for the big shot. Stokes obliges and looks to play the slog sweep but misses.
On off, pushed to cover.
SIX! Hammered! Very good batting from Stokes! He moves to 46 now. Loopy ball around off, Stokes powers it over wide long on for a maximum.
Flatter ball on middle, Pope works it to mid on.
Full on off, Pope defends it to cover.

NOT OUT! Ollie Pope is safely home! Indians are not looking very excited. Full on middle, Pope uses his feet and then works it to mid on and takes off for a quick single. Pujara collects and has a shy at the bowler's end and hits. The third umpire is called for and the replays show that Pope was well in.
Flatter on middle, Stokes nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on middle, Stokes flicks it to the leg side.
Flatter on middle, Ben is solid in defense.
Flighted ball on middle, Pope uses his feet and then flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted ball outside off, Ben lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Ben.
Tossed up on off, Stokes defends it to cover.
Flatter ball outside off, Stokes looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and it goes to short third man for a single.
Loopy ball on the pads, Pope dances down the track and then works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on middle, Ben goes back in his crease and then defends it to mid-wicket.
Quicker ball on the pads, Stokes pads it away.
Down the leg side, Stokes lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up down the leg side, Stokes looks to sweep but misses it.
Flatter on middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.

FOUR! 24th Test fifty for Ben Stokes! It has been a wonderful innings from the English all-rounder but he would know that the work is not done yet and he will look for a big score. Floated on middle, Stokes goes on his knees and mows the reverse sweep to the deep point region for a boundary.
On the pads, Pope works it to square leg.
Floated on off, Pope defends it out off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Pope uses his feet and then flicks it to short leg. It hits the fielder there and rolls to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Pope defends it out.
Flighted ball on middle, Pope works it down to long on for a single.
Was that a dropped chance? No it was not as the replays show no spike. Loopy ball down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses.
Floated on off, flicked to the leg side for a single.
On middle, defended out.
On off, defended out.
Full on middle, Sokes reverse sweeps it to deep point for a couple.
Flatter ball outside off, Stokes cuts it to deep point for a single.
On the pads, Pope defends it out.
Flatter ball on the pads, Stokes nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted ball on off, Pope defends it to point.
Full on off, Pope dances down the track and then pushes it to mid off for a single.

OUT! LBW! Timely wicket for India and Washington Sundar is the man to provide the breakthrough. Stokes was playing for the spin but it does not and goes on with the angle. End of a good innings from Ben Stokes but he needed to continue on and post a big score. Sundar bowls a floated ball on middle, Stokes looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. India appeal and up goes the finger. Stokes does not take the review and walks back in a dejected manner.
Just short! Flatter ball on middle, Lawrence flicks it uppishly towards short leg where it falls just short of Gill.
Loopy ball on middle, Lawrence looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated on off, Pope pushes it to point.
Flatter on off, Pope goes back in his crease and then pushes it to cover.
Quicker ball on middle, Pope punches it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Pope defends it to silly point.
On off, Pope uses his feet and then pushes it to mid off.
Flatter ball on middle, Lawrence plays it to mid on.
Flighted ball on the pads, Lawrence looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On middle, Dan works it to mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Lawrence plays it to long on and crosses over for a run.
Low full toss on middle, pushed back to Sundar.
Loopy ball on middle, Pope uses his feet and defends it out onto the pitch.
Flighted ball on off, Lawrence looks to defend but gets an outside edge to point.
FOUR! Very good shot from Lawrence! Flighted ball on middle, Lawrence dances down the track and lifts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
FOUR! This will make Lawrence feel really good! Tossed up on off, Lawrence reaches for it and then drives it through the covers for a boundary.
Outside off, cut to point.
Flatter ball on middle, Dan works it to mid-wicket.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Loopy ball on the pads, Lawrence looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. India put up an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Probably going down leg.
Flatter ball on the pads, Pope works it to square leg.
Slower through the air on off, Pope defends it to cover.
On the pads, tucked to short leg.
Full and on middle, Pope plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Pope uses his feet and then drives it back to the bowler.
Loopy on off, Pope once again works it back to Sundar.
Outside off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Loopy ball around off, Pope looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the shoulder.
Tossed up on middle, Pope defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
This is well played by Pope! Flatter ball outside off, Pope waits for it and then cuts it through backward point for a couple.
Loopy ball on off, Pope dances down the track and then looks to flick but it goes off the leading edge towards long off for a single.
Low full toss on off, Pope drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Dan defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Dan plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on off, Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on off, Dan dances down the track and then pushes it back to Ashwin.
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it to cover.
Back of a length ball outside off, Pope plays it to deep point for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Dan.
Good length ball outside off, Dan lets it go to Pant behind the stumps.
Good length ball on middle, Dan defends it to mid on.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Dan shoulders arms to it.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Loopy ball around off, Pope lunges forward and looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. India appeal but the umpire is not interested. Rohit signals from behind that it is turning too much and India do not take the review. Good decision not to review as the Ball Tracker shows that it was going onto miss the stumps.
On off, Ollie uses his feet and then defends it out.
Flighted on middle, Pope sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted on off, Lawrence defends it out.
Full on off, Lawrence nudges it down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball outside off, Pope pushes it wide of mid off for a single.
BYE! Good length ball down the leg side, Pope looks to flick but misses. Pant fails to collect and the batters collect a bye.
Full on middle, Lawrence flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Lawrence rides the bounce and defends it out onto the pitch.
Very full on the pads, Dan flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Lawrence pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! What a way to end the session for England! Full on middle, Lawrence creams the drive through mid on for a boundary. TEA ON DAY 1.
Siraj starts with a good length ball on off, Pope defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Pope mistimes it to mid off for a dot.
On a length on off, Pope pushes it to cover off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Ollie plays it to cover and takes a quick run.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky for Lawrence as it was in the gap! Fullish ball outside off, Lawrence looks to push at it but it takes the outside edge and it goes just past Rohit Sharma at gully for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Dan nudges it to mid on.
Full on middle, Pope plays it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Vey well played by Lawrence! He is looking in good nick at the moment! Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence moves inside his crease and then drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Flatter ball on middle, Dan defends it back to the bowler.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Tossed up around off, Lawrence prods forward and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. India appeal but the umpire says no. Ashwin is in a long discussion with the keeper buteventualy decide not to go for the review.
Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence cuts it to point.
On middle, defended out off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Pope works it to deep square leg for a single.
WIDE! Good keeping by Pant! Bouncer around middle, Lawrence ducks under it. Pant jumps and makes a very stop. Wide signalled by the umpire.
Full ball on off, Dan pushes it to point.
Good length ball outside off, Dan lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Lawrence prods forward and defends it to cover.
FOUR! Good looking shot from Lawrence! He has played really well so far but needs to continue! Fullish ball on off, Lawrence drives it through the mid off region for a boundary.
Flatter on middle, Pope defends it to the leg side.
Loopy ball on off, Pope uses his feet and then blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Poor from Ashwin and Pope makes full use of it! Shortish and outside off, Pope cuts it through the backward point region for a boundary.
Floated on off, Pope looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
On off, pushed to the point region for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Lawrence flicks it to deep square leg region for a single.
loopy ball on off, Lawrence nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Lawrence uses his feet and then looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
BEATEN! Superb stuff from Axar Patel! Beauty of a delivery! Loopy ball around off, Lawrence looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flatter ball outside off, cut to point.
Shorter on middle, Dan nudges it to mid-wicket.
On middle, worked to the mid-wicket fielder.

Another appeal for LBW but turned down again! Flighted ball around off, Pope strides forward and looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal is made but the umpire is unmoved. Probably the impact was outside off.
BEATEN! Flatter ball outside off, Pope looks to cut but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SHORT LEG! It has hit the bat, then hit the pad and went straight to short leg. How unfortunate is that? Pope's fight is over. He fought really hard out in the middle but it has been cut short by Ashwin who gets his first wicket of the game. Loopy ball on middle, Pope dances down the track and then looks to flick but it seems to have taken the inside edge, then onto the pads and straight to Gill at short leg, who pouches it safely. The Indians are confident while Pope has a chat with his partner. The umpires converge and take it upstairs. The soft signal is out. The replays roll in and it shows that it is not a bump ball and it has gone off the bat first, then off the pads, straight to Gill.
Full toss on middle, Foakes flicks it wide of mid on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Lawrence plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, nudged to the mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Foakes looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Ben defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Foakes is solid in defense.
Flatter on middle and leg, Ben tucks it to short leg.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled by Axar! Loopy ball outside off, Foakes looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.
On middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Flatter on off, Lawrence defends it out off the back foot.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on the pads, Dan nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on off, Dan defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Dan plays it to long on for a single.
Flatter ball on off, Foakes looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full around off, Lawrence looks to flick but misses and hits him on the pads.
Tossed up on middle, Dan plays it back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Lawrence looks to flick but misses.
Flatter ball on middle, Lawrence works it wide of mid on for a single.
Flatter ball on off, Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Ben prods forward and then plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Lawrence is solid in defense.
Tossed up on off, Foakes works it down to long on for a single.
Flatter ball on off, Foakes taps it to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! Ashwin gets another! Sharp chance for Rahane but he is a very good fielder and makes it look very easy. Foakes does not last long at the crease. Beautiful piece of bowling from Ashwin and England are 7 down now. Ashwin tosses this one around off, Foakes lunges forward and then looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Rahane at first slip. Ajinkya lunges forward and takes a good catch, just inches above the ground. After going wicket-less in the first two sessions, Ashwin is making the ball talk now in the final one of the day.
Flighted ball outside off, Bess uses his feet and looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes towards the point region.
Loopy ball on off, Dom pushes it to cover.
A couple taken! Floated ball outside off, Lawrence drives it to cover where Kohli dives and makes a half-stop. A couple taken as the ball goes to wide long off.
On middle, defended out.
Flighted ball on middle, Lawrence flick it to mid-wicket.
Shortish and outside off, Lawrence punches it wide of the deep cover fielder for a couple.
On middle, Lawrence goes back in his crease and then flicks it to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! The third umpire deems that it has bounced before it hit Gill's boot and then to Pant. Lawrence survives but by just. He was very close to being dismissed in a strange manner but luckily for him and England, he manages to survive. Flatter ball on middle, Lawrence flicks it towards short leg. It seems to have gone off the boot of Gill and into the gloves of Pant. The Indians are confident and are celebrating but the two on-field umpires converge and take it upstairs. The third umpire checks various replays and then finally deems that it has just bounced ahead before it hit the boot of Gill. Lawrence stays to fight it out.
Short and keeping straight. Bess looks to run it down away from slip but misses it.
Flatter on off, Bess taps it to the right of slip.
Tossed up on middle, Bess comes down the track and whips it to mid-wicket for a couple.
Short on the pads, Bess turns it to backward square leg.
Floated on off, Bess pushes it to the off side and rotates the strike.
Short and turning in, Lawrence whips it spin through square leg and keeps the strike with a run.
FOUR! Good from Lawrence! Poor delivery from Axar though! Short ball on middle and leg, Lawrence quickly rocks on his back foot and then pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.

Flighted ball on middle, Lawrence flicks it to the side of the pitch on the leg side and takes off for a single. Axar goes after it but fails to collect it cleanly. In the end, the batters make it back easily.
Flatter ball on middle, Bess works it to the leg side.
Shortish on the pads, Bess nudges it to square leg.
Full on middle, Bess defends it to mid on.
Loopy ball on middle, Dom dances down the track and then flicks it to mid-wicket.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Tough chance for Ashwin, very tough chance as it was travelling pretty quickly for him. Loopy ball on middle, Lawrence uses his feet and then whacks it straight towards the bowler. Ashwin sticks his right hand out but gets only fingertips to it. It goes past the umpire and into the fence.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, Lawrence nudges it to long on for a single.
Flighted on middle and leg, Bess flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter on middle, Bess looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up outside off, Bess uses his feet and then looks to defend but once again gets hit on the front pad.

OUT! STUMPED! Lawrence was looking to be positive but does not connect this time and it is an easy stumping for Rishabh Pant. End of a decent knock but he would be disappointed that he could not carry on. Axar Patel bowls it slower through the air outside off, Lawrence dances down the track and then looks to smack it out of the park but gets deceived by it and misses. Pant collects and has no problems in whipping the bails off. Lawrence is nowhere in the picture. Axar has his third. Can he get another 5-fer?
Flatter ball on off, Leach pushes it to point and takes a single.
On middle, Dom pords forward and defends it onto the pitch.

OUT! LBW! Ball Tracker shows all reds and Axar gets his fourth! Dom Bess departs without making much of an impact and England just one wicket away from getting bowled out. Loopy ball on middle, Bess looks to defend but gets rapped on the pads. India appeal and the finger has gone up. Bess takes the review immediately. There is nothing on Ultra Edge while the Ball Tracker shows all reds so Bess can continue the walk back to the pavilion.
Tossed up on off, Anderson defends it to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Anderson looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
BEATEN! Loopy ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Flighted ball on middle, Leach looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards the leg side for a single.
Full on off, Anderson defends it to cover.
Full on off, Anderson pushes it to cover.

A run out chance missed! Flighted ball on middle, Anderson works it to the leg side. Leach wants the single but Anderson is late in taking off. Axar collects the ball and has a shy at the stumps at the bowler's end but misses. Anderson would have been a goner.
On off, defended out.
Flatter ball on off, Anderson defends it to point.
Flatter ball outside off, James punches it through covers for a couple.
Full on off, pushed to cover.
FOUR! The reverse sweep comes out! Floated outside off, Anderson reverse sweeps it to third man for a boundary.
BEATEN! Nice comeback from Axar! Tossed up ball outside off, Anderson looks to defend but gets beaten.
On off, Anderson plays it to the off side for a single.
Flighted ball on off, Anderson looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes on the bounce to first slip.
On the pads, worked to mid-wicket for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! Loopy ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but misses.
FOUR! Full toss and it has been put away! Full toss outside off, Leach smacks it through the extra cover region for a boundary. 200 up for England.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Jack is solid in defense.
Flatter ball on middle, Anderson defends it out onto the pitch.
Uppish but safe! Flatter ball outside off, Anderson looks to cut but gets a top edge. It lands safely in front of the short third man fielder and a single is taken.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Full on off, Leach prods forward and then plays it to cover.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Leach looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flighted ball on the pads, Jack works it to the leg side for a single.
Flighted ball on off, defended to point.
On middle, defended to silly point.
Flatter ball on middle, Leach defends it out onto the pitch.
Shortish on the pads, Leach nudges it to leg slip.

OUT! LBW! All reds it is and that's the end of the innings! Ashwin ends with three while Axar remains stranded on four. Loopy ball on off, Leach prods forward and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW and the finger has gone up. Leach has opted for the review. There is nothing on Ultra Edge while the Ball Tracker shows all reds. ENGLAND ALL OUT FOR 205.
Anderson starts with an outswinger on off, Gill drives it towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Gill defends it out solidly towards mid on.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is and India lose a wicket in the very first over of their first innings. Gill's poor form continues in this series and he has to walk back. Perfect start for England. This is just what they needed after posting a low score. Anderson bowls a good length ball on middle and leg, Gill looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. England appeal and the finger goes up. Gill has a chat with his partner and then signals the 'T'. There is nothing on Ultra Edge while the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps. Brilliant from Anderson.
Full ball on off, Pujara defends it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara is solid in defense. No run.
Excellent first over from Anderson comes to an end! A wicket-maiden! Full ball outside off, Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
Low full toss on off, Sharma drives it to extra cover. Missed out on a potential scoring opportunity here.
Stokes goes full and outside off, Sharma lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sharma hops and then defends it out.
EDGED AND FOUR! Sharma is off the mark in an edgy manner! Good length ball outside off, Sharma looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and it goes past gully for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Sharma flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Sharma sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it to the leg side.
Full on off, Pujara prods forward and then defends it to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Cheteshwar.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara rocks on his back foot and then defends it out.
Fullish ball on off, Sharma prods forward and then blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, worked to the leg side.
On a length on off, Sharma blocks it solidly towards cover.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on middle, RS is solid in defense.
Back of a length ball outside off, Pujara watches it carefully and then shoulders arms to it.
Fullish ball outside off, Pujara has no problems in letting it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it to mid on.
Fullish ball on middle, Pujara bunts it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara defends it out.
Full ball outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Leach starts with a floated ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Flatter ball on off, Sharma looks to defend but gets a leading edge towards cover. Pujara wants the single but is sent back by Rohit.
Outside off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Good shot for a couple! Full on the pads, Pujara gets down to the pitch of the ball and flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara cuts it to point.
Loopy ball on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma nudges it to the leg side.
On a length on off, Rohit blocks it out onto the pitch.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sharma looks to punch it off the back foot but it goes off the upper half of the bat and rolls to point.
Fullish ball on off, Sharma defends it to cover.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sharma blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on the pads, Pujara uses his feet and then flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a couple.
Tossed up on off, played towards mid off by Pujara.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to Leach.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Pujara defends it out solidly.
Flatter ball on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
FOUR! That's nicely played by Pujara! Flatter ball outside off, Pujara guides it to the third man region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Sharma pushes it to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Rohit.
Good length ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.No run.
Full ball on off, Sharma drives it back to the bowler.
That is 5 maidens in a row for James Anderson! Good length ball outside off, Sharma has no problems in leaving it alone.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara looks to defend but gets an inside edge which goes to the fine leg region for a couple.
Flatter ball outside off, punched to point.
Flatter and outside off, played to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up on off, Sharma attempts to defend but gets an outside edge which goes past the slip fielder for a couple.
On off, defended to cover.
Floated on off, Sharma pushes it to cover.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara uses his feet and then plays it to long on for a single. No Ball signalled by the third umpire.
Short ball on middle, Rohit pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Nearly a wicket! Floated ball on off, Pujara flicks but does so uppishly. Luckily for Pujara, it lands short of the fielder at short leg.
On off, pushed to cover for a single.
Floated ball on the pads, Sharma looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Short ball down the leg side, Sharma leaves it alone.
Flatter ball on middle, Sharma plays it out onto the pitch.
Full on the pads, Pujara uses his feet and then nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on off, Pujara defends it to silly point.
A couple now! Short and outside off, Pujara punches it to deep cover for a couple.
Tosed up on off, Pujara taps it to the first slip fielder.
Flatter ball outside off, Pujara plays it to deep point.
Flatter on the pads, Pujara looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Runs straightaway for Rohit and India. A little too full ball on middle, Rohit flicks it through mid-wicket and scampers back for a couple. Positive start from him.

Ohhh! Rohit got to be careful. That came in a long way after pitching way outside off. Rohit didn't account for the inward movement and he wanted to leave it alone. The ball comes back in and hits him high on the pad.
Just outside off on a good length, this time Rohit gets right behind the line to block it.
Length ball around off, pushed towards backward point.
Full and wide outside off, Rohit goes for the drive but it takes the thick outside edge and goes towards point.
A mild LBW appeal but nothing from the umpire. No review from England. This one once again landed outside off and jagged back in sharply. Rohit looks to defend but got hit high on the pad again.
A back of a length ball around off, Pujara keeps it out off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and wide, asking Pujara to go for the drive. The Indian no. 3 is not keen for offers like these, that too this early in the day.
Good length and outside off, kept out off the back foot.
In the channel outside off, shapes further away. Pujara leaves it alone.
Shortish ball angled in, tucked ont the leg side. A maiden from Stokes to begin.

Rohit gets hit on the pad again. Lovely stuff from Anderson so far. Once again he makes the ball to jag back in. This one pitches around off and middle and comes in to strike Rohit high on the thigh pad.
Rohit waits for the ball to come closer this time and tucks it towards mid on and crosses for a single.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fuller and just outside off, poked on the off side.
Fuller and wider outside off, moves away further after pitching. Pujara makes a leave.
This is just behind good length but wide outside off. Pujara lets it be.
Wide outside off from Stokes. Left alone.
Around off on a length, kept out off the back foot.
Length ball on middle, tucked through mid-wicket for one.
Slips the fuller ball down the leg side. Pujara looks to flick but misses.
Lovely bouncer! The effort ball from Stokes. This is just outside off, Pujara first wanted to defend but at the last moment decides against it.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Around off on a good length, kept out.
Good length ball around off, Rohit blocks off the front foot.
Little too wide outside off, left alone.
Another one wide outside off. Rohit is not interested is playing at that.
Anderson angles this one from outside off. Rohit covers his stumps and lets it be.
Fullish and around off, Rohit pushes it towards mid off.
Runs for Pujara? No, off the pads. Stokes runs in and bowls this one around off, comes back in. Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to square leg and they cross.
Rohit misses out now. A juicy high full toss. Rohit drives but finds the cover fielder.

FOUR! Oh, come on, Stokes! He is Rohit Sharma. Not going to miss out on consecutive full tosses. Stokes serves a wide full toss. Rohit creams it through cover-point and it races away to the fence. First boundary of the morning.
Now bowls one on the pad. Rohit nudges it on the leg side for one.
Around off on a good length. Cheteshwar blocks.
Good length and around off, solidly defended.
Wide outside off, left alone by Rohit.
Fuller and wider this time. Rohit makes a watchful leave.
Too wide again for the batter. Rohit is not keen again.
Fuller ball around off, solidly blocked back to the bowler.
Shapes away after landing just outside off. Rohit leaves it alone.
And again! 5th leave in the over. Anderson need to make the batters play.
Stokes runs in and bowls it wide outside off now. Pujara is not interested.
A jaffa from Stokes! Top stuff. A sharp bouncer around off. Pujara drops his wrists and sways away from the firing line.
Around off on a length, kept out.
Shortish and around off, Pujara blocks.
In the channel outside off, Pujara makes a leave.
Another sharp delivery from Stokes. It is closer to around off. Pujara watchfully leaves it alone.
Fullish and around off, Rohit looks to defend but it goes to mid on off the inner half.
Full and outside off, pushed hard to the man at mid off.
Good length and around off, Rohit takes a big stride forward and defends it towards backward point. Bess there runs to his left and stops the ball.
Fuller and around off again. Played to mid on.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and outside off, Rohit offers no shot again.

What was that? Leach fires the first one down the leg side. Pujara lets it be. Foakes moves to his left and collects. Looks like that was pre-planned delivery. Pujara likes to give the bowler charge early on but here he waited for the delivery.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara slaps it to deep cover for one.
Floated around middle, poked towards mid on.
Beats the bat with a beauty. Floats this one just around off, it lands and spins away to beat the forward defense of Rohit.
On middle, Rohit tucks it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.

Just short of Stokes. Superb ball to end the over. An eventful first over from Leach. Loops this just around off, Pujara comes on the front foot and looks to defend. The ball takes the outside edge after spinning away a touch. The ball goes to Stokes at first slip but falls just short and Stokes takes it on the bounce. Replays show that it hit the gloves of the keeper there. This will go down as a drop then.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rohit swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Quick run! A leg bye. This one is on the pad, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to square leg and they cross for a leg bye.
Back of a length and angling in from outside off. Rohit looks to punch it on the off side but it goes to mid on off the inside half of the bat.
Fuller and outside off, driven towards backward point.
Bouncer! This is just outside off, Rohit sits under it.

Big appeal for LBW but turned down. They discuss for the review but opt against it. Floated around off, Pujara comes down the track and looks to defend. Misses to get hit on the pad. A loud appeal follows but it is turned down. Leach feels that there was some bat. They get togther to discuss the DRS call and in the end opt against it.
Full ball on middle, flicked to square leg for one.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Quick single. This time Rohit jumps out of the crease and flicks it towards mid on. A single taken.
Flat and around off, punched to the man at covers.

OUT! LBW! Three reds shows the Ball Tracker and Pujara has to go. Big, big success for Leach and England. A poor, poor review from Pujara to be honest. He called for it quickly after the umpire raised the finger and did not even discuss with his batting partner. But to his dismay, it is pad first and the ball is crashing into the stumps. This is 4th time Leach has got better of Pujara. This landed around off and spun into Pujara. Pujara comes forward and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. A massive appeal and the umpire quickly raises his finger. Pujara calls for the review straightaway. But not going to work for him. He has to go as it hit the pad first. Waste of a review from him.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, Rohit wanted to leave it alone but was a bit late in doing so. The ball takes the toe end and goes towards the slip cordon.
Close leave! This one came back in sharply after pitching outside off. Rohit covers his stumps and makes a leave.
Another leave as this one is served wide outside off.
And again! Too wide and outside off. Left alone by Rohit.
Shortish and just outside off, punched to the man at covers.
On middle, kept out.
Floated and around off, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, pushed towards the cover region. Wanted a single but opted against it.
Full and around off, Kohli blocks it back to Leach.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Fuller and wide outside off, driven to backward point. Wasn't off the middle of the willow.
Back of a length and around middle, pulled to deep square for one.
Good length and around middle, keeping a bit low. Kohli does well to block it on the leg side.

OUT! TAKEN! Stokes strikes and the Indian skipper has been sent packing for a duck. The crowd has gone silent here. Terrific bowling from Stokes. He kept coming at the batters and in his long extended spell, he has got the big fish. He runs in and bowls it short. It is outside off, Kohli is probably looking to get off the mark. Kohli hops and looks to poke it on the off side and get off the mark. He ends up getting a faint outside edge to the keeper. Foakes makes no mistake. Kohli looks shocked as he stands his ground. The extra bounce did the Indian skipper there. Massive, massive wicket for England here. Two big wickets in the session for the visitors.
Good length and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Full and around off, kept out by Rahane. End of a successful over from Stokes.
Tossed up and wide outside off, Rohit drills the drive to sweeper cover for one.
Floated around off, kept out.
Flat and around off, played back to the bowler.
Around off, Rahane defends.
Rahane is up and running. Flat and just outside off, punched on the off side for a single.
Floated around middle, kept out.
Back of a length ball around off, Rahane taps it to point and comes out for a run. Rohit though is quick to tell Rahane to turn his bike.
Shortish ball around off, Rahane taps it to the right of gully.
Stokes continues to pepper Rahane with the short stuff. Rahane once again is happy to tap it to the right of gully.
Full and wide outside off. There is some movement as Ben tries to tempt Jinks to drive. Rahane is calm as a cucumber and leaves it alone.
Stokes hits the deck hard, Rahane taps it onto the ground.
Classical defense! Full around off, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends it textbook style to see off the over.
Rohit comes down the track and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the pad. There is a stifled appeal from the visitors but nothing from the umpire.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Tossed up around off, Rohit comes down the track and goes inside out over extra cover for a boundary. Just the third boundary in 88 balls for Rohit. Not very often that you see that.
Short around off, Rohit taps it behind point and asks for a run. Rahane turns it down.
Straighter one just outside off. Rohit leaves it alone. Good leave as that one was not far away from the stump.

Bounce! Extra bounce but very well kept. Short around off, Rohit gets on his back foot to play but there is a tennis ball bounce on this. Rohit sways away from it looking at the bounce and loses his balance as well. Foakes does really well to gather the ball. He is also quick to take off the bails as Rohit was struggling for balance but Sharma never went out of the crease.
Floated on the stumps, Rohit keeps it out.
Shortish and on middle and leg, Rahane clips it to deep square leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller and wider outside off. Left alone.

Ouch! That is off the helmet. A sharp bouncer from Stokes once again. Rohit goes for the pull but he is a bit too early. Gets hit on the helmet and the ball goes to fine leg. They cross for a leg bye. Rohit looks fine as he flashes a smile as the umpire calls for the physio.
Full and wide outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Down the leg side. Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball shaping away from around off. Rahane taps it to point and shouts a loud no.
Flighted on middle and off, Rohit defends it.
Slightly short and turning away. Rohit opens the face of the bat and runs it down away from slip for one. Brings up the 50  for India.

FOUR! First boundary for Rahane! A loose delivery from Leach and he gets punished! A rare poor ball from Jack. He goes short on off, Rahane pulls it with power and timing through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Rahane drives it to the right of short extra cover. The fielder there dives and keeps it down to one.
Floated on off, Rohit blocks it.
On the stumps, Rohit keeps it out.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! Absolutely high-class from Rahane. Stokes dishes a full ball outside off. It is over pitched and away from the stump. Rahane is quick to lash onto it as he drives it magnificently through extra cover for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it.
Rahane looks in the mood! Length delivery on off, Rahane pulls it over mid-wicket and gets a brace as Pope cleans it up before the ropes.
Length ball outside off, asking Rahane to go for the drive. The Indian Test vice-captain is happy to eave it alone.
A little zip off the surface for STokes. This is on a length and bounces a tad more. Rahane manages to tickle it behind square leg for one.

Uppish but safe! Good effort from Stokes. Bowls a full ball and manages to get some inward swing as well. Rohit looks to push but the ball hits the inner half of his bat and goes uppishly to the right of Stokes. He dives but cannot get there.
Floated on middle and off, Rahane lunges forward and blocks it.

FOUR! WHIPPED! Short and turning away. Rahane takes the risk of playing it against the spin. He whips it uppishly to the right of short mid-wicket. The fielder there dives but cannot get there and the ball races away to the fence.
Rahane smartly goes back to defending as Leach tosses this up on middle.
Flighted on off, Rahane blocks it.
Tossed up on off, AR keeps it out.
Another whip but this time along the ground and straight to the fielder. Floated on off, Rahane whips it but finds Sibley at short mid-wicket.
Bess starts with a fuller delivery on middle and off. Rohit taps it back to the bowler.
An off-break on middle and off. Rohit turns it with the spin to square leg.
Good work from Pope at short leg. Floated on middle, Rohit turns it to the left of short leg. Pope dives, gets his hands to it, and saves runs for his side.
Bess gives this one some air. Rohit defends it.

FOUR! Rohit takes the risk but commits himself! The ball bounces just inside the ropes. Floated on off, Rohit gets down on his knee and slog sweeps it. There are two fielders in the deep on the leg side. Rohit hits it right between them. The ball bounces just inside the ropes.
Turn and bounce on this one. It is pitched on leg and turns away with some extra bounce. Rohit looks to flick but retracts. Foakes gets his gloves on it but cannot hold onto it.

Anderson comes and straightaway gets the swing. Beauty of a delivery! Too good for Rahane. Full, pitching in the channel of uncertainty around off. Rahane commits on his front foot. The ball though shapes away and beats the outside edge of Rahane's willow.
Full on off and middle, Rahane defends it with a straight bat.
Good running! On the pads, Rahane flicks it through backward square leg. The fielder from fine leg has to make some ground to his left. Rahane sees it and calls for two and gets it with ease.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Full around off, Rahane pushes it right of the meat to the left of mid off. Lawrence there slides and saves runs.
In the air but safe! Fuller around off, this one shapes back in to the right-hander. Rahane chips his flick but gets enough to send it over and away from short mid-wicket fielder. Two taken.
Short on middle and leg. Rohit flicks it to the leg side. The ball bounces in front of Pope at short leg. It hits Pope and goes behind. The batters take a single.
Short on leg, Rahane goes on his back foot and defends it onto the ground to the leg side.
Floated on leg, it is fuller as well. Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Short and turning in. Rahane dabs it onto the ground in front of Pope at short leg.

FOUR! Easy pickings! Bess decides to be generous and gift wraps a boundary to Rahane. A loopy full toss on off, Rahane is happy for the early summer gift from Bess. He has no problems driving this through extra cover for a boundary. That is the problem with Bess. He keeps things tight for 4 balls and then gives away such freebies.
On the pads, Rahane flicks it to the on side and keeps the strike. Looks like we can sneak in another over before Lunch.
Good length ball around off, Rahane defends it.
Down the leg side. Rahane looks to flick but misses. Foakes dives to his left and takes a good take.
Length delivery on off, there is some little late inswing on this one. Rahane taps it to the on side and looks to sneak in a single. Rohit though is in no mood to take any unnecessary risk.
Fullish around off, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anderson gives England their third wicket of the session and ensures that the lunch is a lot tastier for the tourists. 6th time Anderson has got the better of Rahane in Tests. A very good catch from Stokes at second slip as well.  There was swing on offer and that is why Anderson was brought into the attack before Lunch. The veteran pacer does the job for his skipper and his side. Anderson pulls his length back and bowls it in the channel of uncertainty around off. Rahane is committed to his defense. The ball though shapes away and takes the outside edge. It goes dropping to the left of second slip. Ben Stokes, there dives and takes a very fine catch. That will be LUNCH on Day 2!
Anderson bowls it wide outside off and on a good length. Left alone.
Floated on middle, Rohit allows the ball to hit him high on the pad.
Floated around off, Rohit is on the front foot to block.
On middle, flicked wide of the man at mid-wicket. They do not go for the single.
FOUR BYES! This one turns big after lading on middle. It was short as well. Rohit looks to pull but it spins in sharply. Rohit misses, the keeper misses and it goes to the fine leg fence.
Floated on middle, eased down to long on for an easy single.
Floated around off, Pant blocks.
Around off on a length, pushed to mid on.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Back of a length and on middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
Driven firmly but straight to mid off. Anderson serves a full ball around off, Rohit finds mid off.
Good length and around off, Rohit comes on the front foot to defend. The ball takes the inside edge and goes to mid-wicket.
Around off on a length, Rohit is solid in defense. A maiden.
Floated on middle, Pant comes down the track and strokes it down to long on to open his account.
Shortish and outside off, spins in. Pushed to mid on for nothing.
FOUR! Freebie and Rohit is not going to miss out. Full toss outside off, Rohit creams it through the covers and bags another boundary.
Floated around off, played back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Flat and on middle, tucked to square leg for nothing.
Good length and outside off, Pant lets it be.
Good length ball outside off, Pant has a poke but misses.

EDGED AND FOUR! Anderson goes fuller on off, Pant looks to defend but does so with soft hands. The ball shapes away from the southpaw. It catches the outside edge and goes between gully and first slip to the third man fence.
Anderson pulls his length back outside off. Pant looks to defend but misses.
On off, Pant keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Pant leaves it alone. An edgy boundary came of the over. Anderson's figure reads 14-10-11-2! Just unbelievable!
Short around the body, Rohit pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Darted fuller on off and middle, Pant pushes it back to Bess.
Bess gives this one a lot of air and bowls it slow. Pant gets on his front foot and defends it.
Pant comes down the track and takes this fuller. He pushes it to the right of Bess. He gets to the ball and threatens to throw it at the keeper's end but does not.
Loopy ball around off. Pant comes down the track and takes it as a full toss. Pant pushes it to the bowler.
Short and very close to the off pole. Pant punches it to sweeper cover and keeps the strike. A much better over from Bess.
Back of a length ball around off, Pant pokes it towards backward point. Wants a single but Rohit loudly says, 'Are nahi', meaning, no, no.
Around off on a length, Pant looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg.
Fullish and around off, kept out.
Length ball around off, Pant defends it out.
Outside off, Pant makes a leave.
Serves a fullish ball around off, Pant defends.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Rohit moves into the 40s. Bess tosses it up and bowls it wide outside off. Rohit leans the drive through extra cover and it races away to the fence.
Slips this one down the leg side. Left alone.
Floated on middle, eased a run through mid off.
Shortish and turning away. Pant waits and then taps it towards point.
Loopy ball just outside off, played back to Pant.
Pant gives it a charge and looks to go big over the off side. Fails to time it well. 'Catch it' is the cry from the keeper but it lands well short of mid off.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed to mid off.

FOUR! BOOM! Too short and too wide. Rohit has been in the middle for a long time now. He crunches it between gpoint and the cover fielder. One of the fielders gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. India trail by exactly 100 runs.
Shortish and on middle, worked on the leg side.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fullish and around middle, kept out.
Good length and outside off, punched to the off side for nothing.
Full toss outside off, Pant comes down the track and hits it down to long off for an easy run.
Uppish but wide! Floated around middle, Rohit looks to defend. The ball spins in a touch. It hits the upper part of the bat and lobs wide of the man at short leg.
Flat and around middle, worked towards the on side.
Floated around middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for an easy run.
Quick single! Floated full and on the pads, Pant comes down the track and hits it hard mid on. Calls for a quick single as it goes wide of Bess who dives to his left but cannot stop.
On middle, Rohit defends calmly.
Around off on a good length. Pant is solid in defense.
Outside off on a good length. Poked towards backward point for nothing.
FOUR! Driven nicely! Second boundary for Pant. A bit too wide and fuller too. Rishabh leans into the drive and hits it through the covers to bag a boundary.
Another fullish ball and it is outside off. Left alone.
Fuller and on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
Full again and outside off again. Pant drives but finds the cover fielder.
Floated around off to begin, kept out off the front foot.
Full and on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for one. Rohit moves to 49.

WOW! Stunning stroke! Stunning fielding. Superb cricket overall. Looped ball on middle and leg, Pant brings out the reverse sweep. Nails it wide of the man at deep covers. Crawley there makes a good ground to his right and makes a fine save. Two saved.
On off, played to mid off.

SIX! BANG GOES PANT NOW! He doesn't want Root to settle. Tossed up and around off and middle, Pant puts the dancing shoes on and bangs it over mid off for a biggie. He moves to 20 and the stand between the two moves to 41.
Loopy and around middle, Pant keeps it out.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards the gully region where the fielder makes a fine stop.
Outside off on a length, pushed towards backward point for nothing.
Shortish ball around middle, tucked on the leg side of the wicket.
Fullish and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Angles the length ball from middle, Rohit looks to work it on the leg side but he squares up a touch and the ball goes towards the cover fielder.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Rohit will have to take the long walk back to the pavilion on 49. Massive, massive wicket. It is that man Stokes again. He can do no wrong with the ball. Lovely delivery from Stokes. He gets this ball to jag back in sharply after pitching outside off. Rohit is late in getting his bat down. He gets hit on the back leg. A massive appeal follows and the finger goes up. Stokes roars. He is fired up and why wouldn't he be. This is such a huge wicket. Rohit after having a discussion with his partner goes for the review. Replays roll in. Ultra Edge detects nothing. Ball Tracker time now. Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. The review remains but Rohit has to go. A fine effort but India needed him to go big.
Flat and on middle, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, poked through backward point for one.
Soft hands from Ashwin. A shortish ball around off, Ashwin stays back and pokes it past the man at slip. Two taken.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Loopy ball around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
Darted on middle and leg, spinning in. Ashwin fends it to the man at short fine leg. He wanted a single but a loud no from Pant.
Fuller ball on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on who runs to his left and dives to stop. Single taken.
Shortish and around middle, Ashwin looks to defend but ends up getting a soft leading edge. The ball drops just in front of him.
Slips this one down the leg side. Ashwin misses out on the flick.
FOUR! Gift! This time from Stokes. Full toss and wide outside off, Ashwin said thank you and creams it through the covers.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good bumper to end the over! This rises off the deck from good length. Ashwin wanted to sit under it but was late. The ball hits the bat and drops on the leg side. They cross for a run.
Floated around off, Ashwin blocks.
Flat and just outside off, kept out.
On middle, worked towards the leg side for nothing.
Flat and just around off, Ashwin is solid in defense.
Short and wide outside off, Ashwin looks to punch it on the off side but misses.
This time Leach gives the ball a lot of air. Ashwin comes on the front foot to block. A maiden from Leach.
Back of a length ball around off, pulled to deep square leg for one.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Ultra Edge. Ashwin survives. That was a lovely ball from Stokes. A sharp bouncer it was from Stokes once again. Ashwin looks to run it down to the third man region for a single. However, he misses and the ball goes behind. Foakes collects and England celebrate. Ashwin quickly calls for the DRS. Here comes the replays. Looks really close as the ball goes past the bat. Ultra Edge will clear things. Here it comes. Nothing on it. The sound was the ball hitting the shoulder. Ashwin survives. Good use of the DRS from Ashwin.

EDGY FOUR! Ashwin would've had his heart in his mouth there. Stokes runs in and serves a length ball outside off, Ashwin goes for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the slip cordon and the ball races away to the fence.
Good length and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
On a length and outside off, kept out.
Wide outside off, Ashwin watches it go behind.

Overthrows! Leach vs Pant and the Indian keeper has already used his feet. Pant comes down the track and looks to push it to mid on. He misses and gets hit on the pad. They take a leg bye. There is an unnecessary shy at the stumps which allows them to take an extra run.
Floated around off, Pant sweeps it to short fine leg.

EDGED BUT SAFE! This one spins off the rough. Pant looks to defend off his back foot but gets a little inside edge. It lobs off his pad to the left of Foakes. He is wrong-footed but still dives. Unfortunately for the visitors to no avail.
On the pads, Pant flicks it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Tossed up around off, Ashwin keeps it out.
Short and turning away, Ashwin taps it to point.
Full outside off, Pant drives it straight to Bairstow at short cover.
Slower ball from Stokes but he misses his line and bowls it down the leg side.
Back of a length ball around off, Pant runs it down to third man for a single.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it right of the middle but it is straight to square leg.
Stokes hits the deck hard outside off. Ashwin looks to defend but then pulls his bat back inside the line.
Bouncer! Ashwin ducks under it.
Spinning in a bit. Pant goes on his back foot and defends it.
Short around off, Pant whips it with the spin through mid-wicket. Pant needed two but Aswin says no. Pant in the stump mic, can be heard, saying good call.
Floated on middle, Ashwin defends it on the front foot.
Good running! Leach bowls this slower and gives this air on off. Ashwin nudges it towards point and gets a single.
FOUR! Nicely punched and the trail now is 60! Short and spinning in, Pant goes on his back foot and punches it against the spin through covers for a boundary.

DROPPED! Harsh but technically a drop. Would have been a spectacular catch. Short on the pads, Pant flicks it uppishly but also very hard. Pope at short leg, gets his hands to it but cannot hold onto it. That was hit very hard so was never going to be easy at all.
Short on middle, Ashwin tucks it to the on side.
Back of a length delivery around off, Ashwin taps it to point.
BS continues to hit the deck hard on middle. Ashwin defends it.

NOT OUT! The dive has saved Rishabh Pant! Good cricket all-around. Another good indipper from Stokes. It is on middle and off, Ashwin manages to get bat on ball. The ball goes to the on side. Ashwin calls for the run straightaway. Pant is quick to respond. Bairstow gets to the ball quickly and scores a direct hit. Pant puts in a dive and that sees him get back in time.
On off, kept out.
Length ball on off, Pant defends it to the off side and looks to steal a quick single. Ashwin though is quick to turn it down. No need to take any risky runs here.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jack Leach gets the wicket but where has this come from? Ashwin and Pant both were looking good out in the middle and this one has somewhat come against the run of play. Jack Leach has bowled well and worked hard and has got his reward. Floated delivery on the pads, the ball stops on the surface before coming to Ashwin. He looks to flick it to the leg side and give the strike to Pant but because the ball stops on the surface, Ashwin's flick is uppish and straight to Pope at short mid-wicket. He makes no mistake and India 6 down and they still trail by 59. Second wicket of the session. Can England get another one before the end of this session?
Flatter on off, Sundar taps it to point.
Flighted around off, Sundar lunges forward and plays it to the left of Leach. He dives and denies Sundar the single.
Tossed up on pff, this time Sundar drives to the right of the bowler. Leach dives again and keeps Sundar waiting on a duck.
Floated on off, Sundar is keen to get off the mark. He comes down the track and hits it back to Leach.
Flighted on leg, Sundar defends it to see off the over. Wicket maiden for Leach.
Straighter one outside off. Pant leaves it alone.
