Floated around off, Pant looks to play the reverse sweep but gloves it to point.
Floated on off, Pant pushes it to the off side for a run.
Short around off, Sundar cuts it through point and gets off the mark with a single.
Short and little bit of bounce to go with the turn. Pant blocks it.
Short outside off, Pant knocks it to long on and keeps the strike.
Floated on off, Root gets a little turn. Pant does well to defend it off his back foot.
On the pads, Pant whips it behind square leg and gets a couple to bring up the 150 for India. They trail by 54.
Around off, Pant punches it to cover and gets one.
Flighted on off, Sundar lunges forward and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Washington blocks it.
Short on off, Washington defends it. Looks like we will have one more over before Tea.

NOT OUT! Pant survives! The ball is hitting the stumps but not enough to reverse the on-field call. Shortish delivery pitching on middle. It pitches and does not spin. It comes quicker. Pant looks to flick it off his back foot. He misses and gets hit on the back foot. There is a huge cry for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Root, Bess, and Foakes have a chat and the skipper takes it upstairs. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows two reds but one yellow. The ball is hitting the stumps on umpire's call. Good enough to save the review but not enough to overturn the decision.
Floated on middle, Pant knocks it to long on for one.
Tossed up on off, Washington defends it.
Flighted on off, Washington keeps it out.
Floted outside off and spinning away. Washington leaves it alone.
Flighted ball outside off, asking Washington to drive but the southpaw is happy to leave it alone and go to Tea unscathed. TEA ON DAY 2!
Loopy ball outside off, driven through the covers for a single by Pant.
Full and around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.
Floated on middle, Sundar defends it on the leg side. A bit of an appeal from Root and from the keeper too. Not out says the umpire. No review. Looked to be inside edge.
Flat and around off, Sundar looks to flick but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad.
Floated around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
Tossed up and outside off, Sundar drives it through the covers for one. The lead now stands at 50.
FOUR! And he begins with a gift for Sundar. Washington won't mind it. A full toss on the pads, Sundar flicks it through mid-wicket and finds the fence.
Dropped short this time. Sundar thumps it to deep cover for one.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Poor bowling from Bess. Short and wide outside off. Pant rocks back and cranks it through the covers. It races away to the fence in the deep. He moves into the 40s.
Floated around off, Pant comes down the track and blocks it. Didn't get to the pitch there and did well to keep it out.
Once again he comes down the track and hits it down to long off for a single.
Floated around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.
Shortish ball on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one. Pant wanted the second but they opted against it.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Flat and around off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Floated full and around off, kept out.

Big turn! This one lands just outside off and spins away sharply. Sundar comes on the front foot to block but the ball spins away to beat the outside edge. Foakes collects and takes the bails off in a flash but Sundar never went outside the crease.
Flat and around off, kept out. Tight over from Root.
Full ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Slower fuller ball around off, Sundar defends.
Floated outside off, spins a touch away further. Left alone by Sundar.

Confusion but safe in the end. Had he hit, could have been a big, big wicket for England. A full ball around off, Sundar drives it towards mid off. Pant wants a single but is sent back. Lawrence has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses as Pant dives to make his ground. The throw hits Pant near the shoulder.
Loopy and around off, pushed to mid off.

FOUR! Up and over! Fine shot from Sundar. Tossed up and outside off, he drives it uppishly over the man at covers who leaps to catch but Sundar times it nicely. The ball goes to the fence in the deep. Good way to end the over.
On middle, clipped towards square leg for one.
Floated on middle and leg, Sundar looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flat and outside off, poked towards backward point for nothing.
Flat again. This is around off, Sundar pokes it back to the bowler.
On middle, Sundar defends it solidly.
Shortish ball around off to begin from Leach. Clipped through mid-wicket for one by Pant.
Shortish and on the pads, worked towards fine leg for a run.
Down the leg side, Pant misses his flick.
Short around middle, Pant looks to defend off his back foot but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
On middle and short, Pant blocks.
Flighted on off, Pant pushes it to point and takes the first one quickly. He wants the second but Sundar is in no mood to take the chance against the arm of Stokes.
Flatter on off, Pant defends it to point.
Short around off, Pant taps it to the left of cover-point and gets a single.
Short around off, Washington punches it to the right of Leach at cover.
Tossed up on the stumps, Washington blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Sundar defends it.
Flighted on off, Washington drives it to mid off and keeps the strike with a good single.
Floated on off, Washington blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Sundar defends it.
Impact outside! Floated outside off, Sundar leans forward to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad. Foakes is the only one going up in an appeal.
Leach is bowling too short here. This is knocked to long on for a single.
NO BALL! Short on middle, Pant pulls it to deep square leg and gets a single. Moves to 49 with that. Leach has also overstepped here.
Tossed up on off and middle, Washington milks it to long on and gives the strike to Pant.
Dot to finish teh over. Pant is stranded on 49. Floated around off, Pant plays it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Sundar pushes it to mid off.
Short on off, Sundar whips it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. Takes the partnership to 37 and reduces the trail to 22.
Arm ball outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
Floated on off, Sundar defends it off the front foot.
Again short on the pads. Sundar whips it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.

Appeal for LBW but turned down and Root does not take the review. Darted quicker around off, Sundar looks to defend but seems to have missed it and the ball hits the pad. There is an appeal but the umpire is no interested.
On the pads, Pant flicks it but to short leg.
Short on the pads, Pant tickles it to short fine leg.
Quicker on off, Pant defends it with a straight bat.

FIFTY FOR PANT! His 7th in Tests and 3rd in this series. This has been a very good knock from the young keeper. He is enjoying a rich vein of form and he has done the job fantastically. His innings might be the difference between winning and losing. On a pitch where most batsmen are struggling, he has looked very comfortable. Only Indian batter in this innings to get to a fifty. On the pads, Pant comes down and whips it to the on side for a single.
On the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for an easy single.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortsih ball on middle, worked towards fine leg for one.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket by Pant.
Close leave, a good one at that. That wasn't too far away from the off pole. Darted just outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Short and wide outside off, crunched straight to the man at backward point.
Loopy ball around off, Pant is solid in defense of the front foot.
Floated on middle, Sundar takes a stride forward to block.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, flicked to mid-wicket for one.
Full ball on middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
Another easy run! Flat and on middle, it is worked through backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! SHOT! WHIPPED BY PANT! Loopy fuller ball on middle, Pant flicks it over square leg. One bounce and into the fence. India trail by just 10 now. The stand moves to 49 between the two.
Full and on middle, played back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Flat and around off, Sundar pushes it off his back foot on the off side.
Shortish and just outside off, punched through the covers for one. 50-run stand is up between the two. Fine, fine association for India between the two.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Another one fired outside off. Pant leaves it alone.
Good length and just outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Bouncer on middle and leg. Sundar sits under it.
In the channel, just outside off. Watchful leave from Sundar.
Sharp bouncer! Sundar sways away from the firing line.
Fullish ball around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for an easy single.
Back of a length and just around off, Pant wanted to go for the pull but at the last moment decided against it and punched it to mid off.
Floated on middle, Sundar looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball outside off, driven towards the cover region.
Flat and around middle, kept out off the back foot.
Floated around off, Sundar is solid in defense.
Fired on middle and leg, kept out by Washington.

Big turn! Tossed up and outside off, lands and spins away sharply as Sundar looks to go big, inside out. Makes no connection. The ball hits the gloves of Foakes and lobs up to the left side of Stokes who does well to catch. There was no bat though.

FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard. A length ball outside off, Pant goes for the cut but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the second slip fielder and into the third man fence. 200 up for India.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! That is off the middle of the bat. The scores are level now. Stokes runs in and bangs it short. Pant nails the pull and hits it along the ground. It goes to the deep square leg fence.
Full and wide outside off, driven wide of mid off for two. India are into the lead now.
Angled in from middle, Stokes tucks it to deep mid-wicket and takes one.
A beamer now! Stokes asks for an apology from the batter straightaway. Clearly he is frustrated now. A high full toss. Sundar does well to fend it away.
In the channel outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
Full and outside off, Pant comes down the track and hits it towards the short cover fielder.
Floated outside off, spinning away. Pant lets it be. Looks like anything in his zone will wallop over the fence.

EDGY FOUR! More frustration for England and Stokes. Tossed up and outside off, Pant gors for the slog sweep. He ends up getting it off the toe end. The ball goes over the keeper. Stokes from the first slip gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
FOUR! This time off the meat of the willow. What a blow from Pant. Tossed up and on middle, he gets down and nails the sweep. All along the ground and into the fence at deep square leg.
Short and wide outside off, cut towards backward point.

NOT OUT! Missing the stumps. Pant is safe and he will continue his battle. It was the slider from Root. Pant stayed back in and tried to flick but missed to get hit on the back leg. A loud appeal but turned down by the umpire. The skipper has a word with his keeper and Stokes and they go for the review. Looked really close. Let's see what the replays have got to show. Ultra Edge first, to confirm if there was any bat. Clear gap between bat and pad. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Missing. Pant survives. England lose their review.
Good length ball on middle, Washington defends it.
Length delivery on off, Sundar defends it to mid off.
Stokes hits the deck hard outside off, Sundar punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Another single. This time Pant runs it down to third man and gets a single to move to 75.
Short ball outside off, Sundar sways away from it.
FOUR! Supreme from Washington! Stokes obverpitches it on middle. Sundar drives it through mid on. Stokes flies but to no avail. The ball goes to the fence.
FOUR! Welcome to the attack, new ball and Anderson! Pant comes down the track and smacks it over mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! SLAPPED! Length ball outside off, Pant swots it through covers for a boundary. This is top-class batting from Pant!
Fuller around off, Pant drives it straight to the cover fielder.

What a jaffa! Superb comeback from Anderson. He hist the deck hard and makes the ball shape just a bit away from the southpaw. Pant looks to defend but that extra zip off the surface and little movement sees him miss it.
Fuller on off, Pant pushes it to mid on for one.
Good length ball around off, Washington taps it to point. 9 off the first over from the second new ball. Not the start England would have wanted. The lead now stands at 27!

FOUR! WOW! This is just too good from Pant at the moment. A fuller ball outside off, Pant goes for the drive but fails to connect it well. But he goes throught he shot. It takes the inside edge and goes wide of the man at mid on. And guess what? It goes to the fence.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed wide of mid off for one.
FOUR! Classy from Sundar now. These two are turning things on here. A short ball from Stokes and it is wide as well. Sundar crunches the cut through point and bags another boundary.
Gets behind the line of the delivery this time to solidly block it.
FOUR! Third boundary in the over. Poor from Stokes. Short and wide outside off, Sundar slashes it over gully and finds the fence again.
Wide outside off on a length. This time Sundar makes a leave. 13 off the over. 22 off the first 2 overs off the second new ball.

FOUR! WOW! Pant! What a player! A reverse sweep against a pacer. Against a pacer of the quality of Anderson. Genius. Fullish ball around off, Pant nails the the reverse sweep and hits it over the slip cordon for a boundary. 100-run stand is up between the two as well.
Shortish and around off, Pant taps it on the off side and calls for a single but Sundar is not keen. And that makes Pant unhappy.
Gives the bowler a charge this time but fails to connect and gets hit high on the pad.
Short ball, Pant swivels and pulls it to fine leg for a single. 250 up for the hosts.
Back of a length and on middle, Sundar tucks it towards deep mid-wicket and scampers back for two more.
Length ball around off, worked towards mid-wicket for nothing.

SIX! CENTURY FOR PANT! Century with a biggie! Take a bow, young man. What an unbelievable knock this has been from him. He has just grown in stature ever since his return to the Indian Test side. This man is just too good. A fine, fine knock, one that has been challenging. He walked in when the team was in big, big trouble but he has bailed them out and now have taken them to a strong, strong position. The crowd has gone mad in the stadium. And what a shot to get to the milestone. Root comes in and tosses the ball around middle, Pant gets down and mows the sweep over deep backward square leg for a biggie. Takes the helmet off and raises the bat. Sundar gives him a hug. This is Pant's 3rd Test ton, first in India.
Flatter and just outside off, punched towards the cover region.
Fuller and outside off, driven through the covers for one.
On middle, kept out.
Floated on middle, played back to the bowler.
On middle again. Sundar blocks off the front foot.

OUT! TAKEN! Pant falls now! But not before playing a majestic Test ton. Take a bow, champion. He is mighty disappointed as he heads back to the pavilion. The crowd is standing to appreciate the show-stopper. You live by the sword, you die by it. Pant loves this quote and he often lives up to it. A shortish ball outside off, Pant looks to drag the pull on the leg side. He though ends up hitting it off the toe end. The ball goes straight to the English skipper who makes no mistake. End of a magnificent knock from Pant. He is disappointed big time as he walks back. Hits his pad with the willow but what a knock. India lead by 54.
In the channel outside off, Axar lets it be.
Too full and around middle, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, driven wide of the man at mid off who makes a sliding half stop to his right. A single taken.

FOUR! Shot of the day? Surely one of the contenders. A length ball just outside off, Sundar punches it on the up and hits it wide of the man at mid off. This time the fielder cannot stop to his right.
Just outside off on a length, poked on the off side for nothing. 5 runs and a wicket from the over.
On off, played back to the bowler.
FOUR! Hammered! Too short from Root and Axar nails the pull through mid-wicket. A boundary for him.
Fired on middle, tucked towards the man at short leg.
On off, Patel comes on the front foot to push it back to Root.
Floated on middle, kept out.
Looped up and outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
FOUR! Sundar moves to 48. A stunning stroke to get there. Fuller ball outside off, Sundar slams it through backward point and finds the fence.

FIFTY FOR SUNDAR! Wonderful innings from the young man. His third in the format. A fuller ball outside off, Sundar steers it past the man at gully. It is racing to the fence. However. Bess runs to his right and makes a fine stop with a dive. Saves two but Sundar gets to his half-century.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep point for a single.
Banged short but down the leg side. Patel looks to pull but misses.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Short and wide outside off, cut to deep point for one.
Leach arrives and beats the bat straightaway. Tosses it up and just outside off, Axar looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Turning in from middle, Axar looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Loopy ball outside off, Axar looks to drive but the ball spins in and takes the inner half. Goes to mid-wicket.
Flat and around off, Axar blocks nicely.
Looped up and outside off, Patel is on the front foot to block.
Floated around off, Sundar blocks off the front foot.
FOUR! Another gift from Bess. This hasn't been his day to be honest but then you cannot bowl dollies like this at this level. Juicy full toss, Sundar strokes it over Bess and finds the fence.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
On off, solidly kept out.
Full ball outside off, driven towards the cover fielder who makes a diving stop.
Tossed up and outside off, Sundar gives him a charge and looks to flick it on the leg side. Ends up getting a leading edge that goes to deep cover for one.
Flat and around off, turns in. Sundar clips it through mid-wicket for one.
WIDE! Slipped down the leg side. Axar looks to flick but misses.
On off, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Floated full and around off, played back to the bowler.
FOUR BYES! Foakes cannot collect this one. This one lands on middle and spins in sharply. Patel cannot flick. Foakes cannot collect it down the leg side. Goes to the fine leg fence for four byes.
FOUR! Axar goes for the shot now! Tossed up ball on middle, Axar hits it through the line and does so over square leg. A couple of bounces and into the fence. 9 off this over.
Loopy fuller ball outside off, driven to the cover region.
Floated around off, Sundar comes on the front foot and blocks.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, poked off the front foot towards the cover region.
On off, Sundar blocks.
Floated around off, kept out by Sundar. A much-better over from Bess. A maiden from him, his first of the innings.
On middle, kept out.
Flat and around off, pushed on the off side for nothing.
Floated on off, spins in. Axar looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to leg gully.
Short and spinning in from outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for one.
Shortish and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one more easy single.
Flat and around off, Patel is solid in defense.

In the air... safe! Sundar would've had his heart in his mouth. Good from Bess again. Teases the batsman with a tossed up ball outside off, Sundar looks to go big over the off side but the ball spins away and Sundar ends up slicing it high in the air. However, it keeps going away from Anderson who tries to get under it form mid off. He cannot get there. Two taken.
On off, blocked.

NOT OUT! Sundar is safe! He never want out. That was lovley ball from Bess though. He lands it around off and it spins away to beat the forward prod of Sundar. Foakes collects and takes the bails off. The square leg refers it upstairs.
Floated full and around off, Sundar comes on the front foot to block.
Flat and around middle, Sundar blocks.

NOT OUT! Big spike off the bat. Sundar is safe and he used the DRS nicely. Bess bowls a lovely ball again. Lands it around middle and in spins in sharply. Sundar looks to keep it out but misses to get hit on the pad. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Sundar is quick to signal the 'T'. Time for the replays. Well, well, Bess has to wait for his first wicket. Ultra Edge shows big spike. Excellent use of the review.
Beaten! Flat and just outside off, Patel looks to force it on the off side but misses.
Loopy ball around off, kept out.
Flat and around middle and leg, it keeps low. Axar does well to get his bat down in time to block.
Appeal again but turned down. England are not going for the DRS. This one is tossed up wide outside off, Axar brings out his pad and pushes it away. An appeal for LBW but turned down.
Floated full and down the leg side. Axar looks to flick but misses. Foakes does superbly well to collect to his right. Just one ball left for Axar to negotiate.
And he does that nicely. Floated full and around off, Axar comes on the front foot and blocks it. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Anderson starts with a good length ball outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Sundar watches it carefully and then lets it go to the keeper.
Washington Sundar is in no hurry! Another on a length delivery outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sundar once again has no problems in letting it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Sundar makes another leave to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent ball to end the over! Good length ball around off, it nips away a touch. Sundar looks to defend but it whizzes past the outside edge and goes to the keeper.
An inside edge! Lovely start from Bess! Tossed up ball on off, Axar Patel looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Was in the air for a while but wide of the bowler! Flatter ball on off, Patel punches it uppishly but wide of the bowler and into the long off fence for a boundary.
Loopy ball on off, Patel defends it to cover.
Slower through the air outside off, Axar lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish and on off, Axar moves inside his crease and then punches it through the cover region for a single.
Floated ball on off, Sundar strides forward and then plays it back to Bess.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Patel.
Back of a length ball around off, Patel looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes to the gully region.
On a length outside off, Patel lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball around middle, Patel does well to duck under it.
Fullish ball way outside off, Patel lets it go to Foakes. Anderson has to make the batsmen play more often here.
Going down leg. Good length ball on the pads, Patel looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A mild appeal is made for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
SIX! Excellent shot from Sundar! Brings up 300 in style! The lead moves to 100 as well. Flighted ball on middle, Sundar smacks it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
FOUR! This is even better by Sundar! Such superb timing! Bess struggles to find his rhythm. Low full toss on off, Sundar lunges forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
Flatter ball outside off, Sundar cuts it to point.
Loopy ball outside off, Sundar shoulders arms to it.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar goes back in his crease and then defends it onto the pitch.
Full on off, Sundar drives but the short cover fieder does well to dive and stop it.
Good length ball on off, Patel looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes towards the slip cordon.
Full ball on middle, Patel drives it wide of mid on and takes a run.
A bouncer around off, Sundar looks to fend it away but misses as the ball goes to Foakes behind the stumps.
On a length on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Shortish on the pads, Sundar works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length on the pads, Patel flicks it to the leg side and crosses over for a run.
Flighted ball on off, Patel pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Played well! Calls for a catch but it is over the fielder! Flighted ball on middle, Patel smacks it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Flighted ball on middle, Axar flicks it to square leg.
On the pads, Patel looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On off, defended out.
FOUR! Brilliant from Axar Patel! Flatter ball outside off, Patel rocks on his back foot and then punches it  through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Sundar looks to flick gets a top edge and it goes off the top half of the bat and onto the pitch.
Short ball on middle, Sundar pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Bouncer! It is bowled around middle, Patel ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, Patel defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! That's well bowled by Anderson! Fullish ball outside off, Patel looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Short ball around middle, Patel ducks under it.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Sundar prods forward and then defends it to cover.
Loopy ball on off, Sundar works it down to long on for a single.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Flighted ball on off, Patel prods forward and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Slower through the air on middle, Axar flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Patel flicks it to square leg.
Flatter ball on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but it brushes his pads and it goes to the leg side for a leg bye.
Fullish ball on off, Patel prods forward and blocks it to cover.
PLAY AND A MISS! Another excellent delivery from James Anderson! Full ball outside off, it moves away late. Full ball outside off, Patel looks to drive but misses.
On middle and leg, pushed to mid on.
Short ball around middle, Patel ducks under it.
Fullish ball on the pads, Axar works it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on middle, Sundar uses his feet and then flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! Hammered! Flat six from the bat of Axar Patel! Flighted ball on off, Patel lifts it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Flatter ball on middle, Axar nudges it to short leg.
On middle, nudged down to long on for a single.
Flighted ball outside off, Sundar pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Patel looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the leg side.

Stokes starts with a very full ball on middle, Sundar looks to dig it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Stokes discusses with Root whether to take the review but decide against it.
Short ball around middle and leg, Sundar sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle, Sundar punches it back to the bowler.
LEADING EDGE BUT SAFE! Full ball on the pads, Sundar looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes past the cover fielder for a single.
Back of a length ball down the leg side, Axar looks to flick but seems to have missed it. Foakes appeals but he is the only one doing so. The umpire as well is not interested.
Full on off, Patel plays it back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Sundar heaves it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That was hit very hard! Brilliant batting from Sundar! Full on off, Sundar smacks it straight towards the bowler. It goes in between Leach's legs and goes for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Sundar defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on off, Sundar defends it to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Sundar plays it out to the off side.
Full on off, Sundar uses his feet and then nudges it down to long on for a single.
Very full ball on the pads, Sundar flicks it to fine leg and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Fullish ball on off, Sundar pushes it to cover.
Short ball around middle, Sundar sways away from it. Well played by Sundar.
Shortish outside off, Sundar lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball on middle, Sundar pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple. Sundar has equalled his highest score in Tests.
Good length ball on middle, Washington defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Terrific start from Root! Floated ball outside off, it spins away. Axar looks to defend but misses.
Full on off, Patel pushes it to mid off.
Full on the pads, Patel works it wide of mid on for a single.
Low full toss on off, pushed to the off side.
Flatter ball outside off, Sundar punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full on off, Patel defends it out.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Edged but safe! An effort ball, gets it to rise, Axar looks to fend at it but the ball hits the splice and goes through the vacant gully region, down to third man for one.
Shorter this time again, Sundar pulls, not in total control but hits it well enough to get it over square leg. There is a fielder in the deep so just the one.
One more short one, Axar picks it early and ducks under it.
5 short balls in a row now! Again ducked under.
Patel this time gets on top of the bounce and defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Nicely tossed up outside off, it turns away. Axar looks to go over covers but is beaten.
Fires it on middle, it is worked to mid on.
Outside off, extravagant turn as it lands but it is from outside off. Left alone.
Shorter and on middle, Patel pulls it through mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! Quicker and outside off, Sundar looks to play it late but is beaten.
A short one on middle, Patel ducks under it.
One more short one, Patel evades it.
Pulls it this time, nicely controlled and through square leg for one.
One more short one, this time Sundar pulls it through square leg for one.
Another short one, Patel nudges it towards the leg side.
Shorter one to end, this does not get up a lot. Patel sways away from it.
A little too full, it is hit through covers for one.
Outside off, Patel cuts but finds point.

TWO BYES! This lands in the rough outside off. Patel goes hard at it. It pitches, spins and then takes off. Foakes has no chance, Stokes to fails to stop it as he dives to his right from first slip. Two taken as it goes down towards third man.
Safe! Outside off, Patel lofts it over covers. Takes two. Lead now 150.
Fuller and on off, Patel hits it hard down to long on and takes one.
On middle, it is blocked nicely.
One more short one, it is ducked under.
A bumper again, Patel hops and pulls it through mid-wicket for one. He played it nicely, all along the ground.
Short and outside off, Sundar lets it go through to the keeper.

Really good shot and very good fielding too! The 100-run stand is also up and this partnership is taking the game away from England completely. This is short and on middle, Sundar pulls it with one leg up in the air through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep makes good ground to his right, dives, stops it and then lets it go as he nears the ropes. They go upstairs to check and replays show that he has saved a run for his side.
Angled into the body, it is worked to mid-wicket for one.
Another single as this is pushed down to long on.
This lands outside off and then spins away. Sundar plays inside the line and lets it go.
A full toss, Sundar whips it down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, Patel stays back and pushes it through covers for one.
Outside off, not played at.
One more delivery well wide outside off, it is left alone again.

OUT! The dive does not save Axar! He is a goner. 7 short of his first Test half ton. He is gutted as he walks back. Batted so well till now but he has to go in an unfortunate manner. That is the only way this partnership looked like it will be broken. Coming to the ball now, it is a low full toss, Sundar hits it hard to mid on. Axar wants a run and charges out. He is sent back though as that was hit really well and there was no run in it. Bairstow there picks the ball and throws it to Root who takes the bails off. An appeal and it is referred upstairs. Axar is disappointed as he makes his way back onto his feet after his dive. Replays roll in and they show that he has to walk back. Can England now take the remaining two wickets quickly?

OUT! LBW! Ishant Sharma goes for a first-ball duck! This looked plumb in front and he has to. Stokes gets his third and Washington Sundar might be thinking that he might be stranded here in the 90s. Stokes goes full on middle, Sharma shuffles across and looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Stokes and England appeal and up goes the finger. Ishant walks back without taking the review.
BEATEN! Good length ball around off, Siraj looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full ball down the leg side, Siraj lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! Washington Sundar misses out on a well-deserved hundred as Siraj fails to survive. Good length ball around off, Siraj looks to defend but misses and the ball rattles the timber behind. Stokes ends up with a 4-fer. Sundar walks back a little disappointed but he has played a wonderful knock. INDIA ALL OUT FOR 365 WITH A LEAD OF 160.
Siraj starts with a good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it through to the keeper.
Full ball outside off, Crawley has once again no problems in leaving it alone.
On a length outside the off stump line, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Siraj gets this one to come back in. He bowls a length ball on middle, Crawley though is up for the challenge as he flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Crawley and England are underway! Good length ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Patel starts with a flighted ball on off, Crawley drives it to mid off.
BEATEN! Lovely ball from Axar! He tosses this one outside off, Crawley looks to defend but the ball spins away a little and beats the outside edge of Crawley's bat.
Flatter ball on the pads, Zak flicks it to the square leg region for a single.
Probably going down leg! Flatter ball on the pads, Sibley looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire says no.
Full on middle, Sibley uses his feet and then looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes towards cover.
Floated ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but gets an inside edge which goes to the leg side. No harm done.
Full delivery on middle, Zak flicks it wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on off, Sibley prods forward and then blocks it to cover.
On a length on middle, Dom works it to mid-wicket.

Good fielding from Washington Sundar! Full ball on the pads, Sibley flicks it to the backward square leg region. Sundar comes across from fine leg, slides and makes a good stop. Keeps it down to a single.
On a length on middle, Crawley flicks it through the square leg region for a couple of runs.

Excellent stop by Siraj! Full ball on off, Crawley drives it crisply towards the bowler. Siraj, on his followthrough dives and does really well to stop. He seemed to have hurt himself in the process and is in some pain. He gets up and walks back along with the physio. LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Axar starts with a full ball on off, Sibley prods forward and then plays it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle, Dom defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Sibley strides forward and solidly blocks it to cover.
Floated ball on middle and leg, Sibley blocks it out onto the bat.
Full on middle, Sibley pushes it back to Axar.
Floated ball outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Ashwin starts with a floated ball on off, Crawley defends it out to the off side.

FOUR LEG BYES! Vicious turn! Nothing much Rishabh Pant could have done there! Flighted ball on middle, it spins a lot. Crawley looks to flick but it brushes his pads and goes to the fine leg region for four leg byes.
On off, pushed to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! Ashwin strikes in his first over and this is the perfect start for India in the second session. Crawley's Test is over and he does not create much of an impact. Ashwin tosses this one up around off, Crawley prods forward to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes to first slip where Rahane pouches it safely. England still trail by 150 runs and have 9 wickets in hand.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SHORT LEG! Bairstow goes for a first-ball duck and England lose two-in-two. Excellent captaincy from Virat Kohli. Kept a fielder there for this shot and it has worked to perfection. End of a tough series for Jonny Bairstow. This is the third duck for him in 4 innings. Flighted ball on middle, Bairstow flicks but it goes uppishly towards short leg where Rohit Sharma takes a good catch. Ashwin is on a Hat-Trick now. What a start for India!
No Hat-Trick for Ashwin! Root plays this full ball on middle to square leg for a single. A brilliant start from Ashwin.
Flighted ball on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball outside off, it spun away. Root watches it carefully and leaves it alone.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Flighted ball on the pads, Root looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire says no. Kohli, Pant and Axar are involved in a discussion about whether to take the review but decide not to. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was umpire's call on hitting the stumps.
Outside off, left alone.
Full on middle, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, pushed wide of mid off for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Root nudges it down to mid on for nothing.
Tossed up on off, Root goes on his knees and then sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Sibley uses his feet and then pushes it to long on for a single.
Flatter on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
On the pads, tucked to the leg side.
Shortish on the pads, Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted ball on off, Root prods forward and then defends it to the cover region.
Quicker ball on middle, Root goes back in his crease and then blocks it out onto the pitch.
Flatter ball outside off, Root punches it to cover-point.
Top edge but safe! Flighted ball on middle, Root looks to sweep but it takes the top edge and goes towards deep square leg where it falls short of the fielder. A couple taken.
Flighted on the pads, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball outside off, Root plays it to cover for a single.
Flatter ball on off, Sibley plays it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Sibley looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Quicker on off, Dom taps it to first slip.
Full on middle, Sibley gets to the pitch of the ball and then flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Flat delivery on middle, Root nudges it down to long on for a single.
BEATEN! Beautiful ball from Ashwin! Flighted ball outside off, Sibley prods forward to defend but gets beaten.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Joe defends it to short leg.
Short ball on middle, Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Sibley works it to short leg.
Floated on off, Dom defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another unfortunate dismissal for England! It was Ollie Pope in the first innings and now it is Dom Sibley in the second. Sibley cannot believe it but he has to walk back. Axar bowls a full ball on middle, Sibley sweeps it hard but it hits Gill on the knees at short leg and lobs up in the air. Pant gets underneath it and catches it safely. The two on-field umpires converge and take it upstairs. The soft signal is out. The replays roll in and they show that it has gone directly off Gill's knees. How unfortunate for Sibley?
Flatter on off, Root defends it out.
On off, defended out.
Tossed up on middle, Root looks to defend but misses. It goes off his pads towards leg slip.
FOUR! Lovely shot from Root! Flatter ball outside off, Root punches it through the cover region for a boundary.
FOUR! This is class from Root! Brilliant from Root! Flighted ball outside off, Root drives it throuhg extra cover for a boundary.
Flatter on the pads, Root tucks it to short leg.
Flatter ball on the pads, Stokes looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Flatter ball on middle, Stokes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Root defends it back to mid on.
On middle, Root defends it out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Root drives it to mid off.
Flatter ball on the pads, Stokes defends it out.
Tossed up on the pads, Stokes defends it out.
Flatter ball outside off, punched to cover.
Full on the pads, Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled by Ashwin! Loopy ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flighted ball on middle, Stokes nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SHORT LEG! Straight to the fielder at leg slip! Poor shot and Stokes won't be proud of the shot. Axar Patel gets his second. England are collapsing big time in the second innings and it looks highly likely that this game will end today itself. Flighted ball on middle, Stokes looks to paddle sweep but does not keep it down. It goes uppishly towards leg slip where Virat Kohli takes a simple catch. Stokes walks back disappointed.
Loopy ball on off, Pope defends it to silly point.
Flatter ball on off, Pope defends it to point.
Flatter ball on middle, OP works it to square leg for a single.
Top edge but safe! Loopy ball on middle, Root looks to sweep but it takes the top edge and it goes to the vacant fine leg area for a couple.
Tossed up on middle, Root looks to defend but it takes an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated on off, Pope looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up on middle, Pope uses his feet and then defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Pope nudges it to short leg.
Full on the pads, Pope flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Flatter ball on the pads, Root pads it away.
Short ball on the pads, Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Very full, Root probably was looking to sweep but then realized that it is a little too full so jams it back to the bowler.
Quicker and fired on middle, this is defended.
Tosses it up on off, Root pushes it to mid off.
Fires it on middle, Root defends it out.
Quicker and on off, Root hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Attacks the stumps again, blocked.
Good length ball on off, Pope pushes it to the point region for a single.
Good length ball on off, defended to point.
On a length on off, Root defends it to cover.
On off, Root gets behind the line of the ball and then blocks it out.
Full ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, defended to cover for a single.
FOUR! Swept and swept hard! Flighted ball outside off, Root drags it from outside off and sweeps it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flatter ball on middle, Root defends it out onto the pitch.
Flighted ball on off, Root defends it to silly point.
Floated on middle and leg, Joe is solid in defense.
Full on off, pushed to point. Kohli tries to throw it back to the keeper but it hits Root near the box. Och!
Floated ball outside off, left alone by Root.
Good length ball on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Ollie works it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Root drives but finds the fielder at mid off.
Full ball on the pads, Root shuffles across and then flicks it through the square leg region for a couple of runs.
On a length on middle, Joe works it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length outside off, Pope looks to defend but it goes off the thickish outside edge past gully for a single.
Full on middle, played towards mid on for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Joe nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on the pads, Root looks to pull but it takes the inside edge and goes to leg slip.
Shortish on middle, tapped to the leg side.
Outside off, pushed to the off side for a single.
Just wide of short leg! Floated on middle, Pope looks to flick but it takes the inner half of the bat and goes past short leg.
Flatter on off, Root defends it out.
Shortish and outside off, it spins away. Root rides the bounce and taps it to first slip.
Floated on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Root punches it to cover.
BEATEN! Beauty from Axar! Root has no clues! Floated outside off, it spins away. Root looks to defend off the back foot but misses.
Quicker ball on the pads, Root looks flick but gets hit on the thigh. A good over from Axar comes to an end.
Flighted ball on middle, Pope reverse sweeps it but straight to point.
SIX! This is a beautiful shot though from Pope! Lovely use of the feet! Flighted ball on middle, Pope dances down the track and then lifts it over long on for a maximum.
Loopy ball on middle, Pope sweeps it to square leg.
Floated on middle, Pope uses the feet and then defends it back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Pope looks to reverse sweep but misses.
Floated on middle, Pope looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Flatter ball outside off, punched to cover.
Loopy ball outside off, this is left alone by Joe.
Tossed up outside off, Root punches it to cover.
Flatter ball on middle, Root works it to the leg side for a single.
Flatter ball on middle, Pope works it to the leg side.

TOP EDGE BUT SAFE! Flighted ball on middle, Pope uses the feet and then looks to sweep but it takes the top edge and goes over the keeper. Rahane gives it a chase and he seems to have pulled it back in. The third umpire is called for to check whether it is a clean save. He checks various replays and finally deems that it is fine. Three taken.
FOUR BYES! Vicious turn! Flighted ball down the leg side, it spins a lot. Pope looks to flick but misses. Pant fails to collect and it has gone to the fine leg region for a boundary.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Pope defends it to cover.
Just wide of the leg slip fielder! Flighted ball on the pads, Ollie looks to flick but it brushes his pads and it goes past the leg slip fielder for a couple of leg byes.
Tossed up on off, spinning in. Pope looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Flighted ball around the pads, Pope looks to play the reverse sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. India appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Full and on off, Root pushes it to mid off for a single.
BEATEN! Another one which has turned viciously! Loopy ball outside off, it spins away a lot. Pope looks to defend but gets beaten.
Loopy ball on middle, Pope looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the leg side.
Another beauty from Axar! Floated ball outside off, Ollie prods forward to defend but misses it completely.

OUT! STUMPED! Excellent work from Pant and Pope has to go! This is excellent bowling from Axar as well. It is his third and Axar keeps on having a great Test series. Flighted ball on off, Pope uses his feet and then looks to flick but the ball turns away and beats the edge of the bat. Pant fails to hold it at first cleanly but still manages to recover and whip the bails off. The third man is called for and the replays show that Pant has done well and Pope is well out. Pant did drop the ball but it was after he whipped the bails off. England 5 down.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! All reds it is and Root has to go! Ashwin gets his third as well. The end is nigh for England. They are in deep trouble and only a miracle can save them now. The big fish, Joe Root goes and takes a review along with him. Flatter ball on middle, Root goes back in his crease and then looks to defend but he seems to have missed it and gets rapped on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW and the finger has gone up. Root takes the review immediately. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows all reds. India just 4 wickets away and they still lead by 95 runs.
Full on middle, Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, defeded back to the bowler.
LEG BYE! Tossed up on middle, Foakes looks to flick but it goes off his pads and goes over the leg slip fielder for a leg bye.
Flatter ball on off, Lawrence defends it to cover.
Flatter on middle, Dan tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Dan defends it to silly mid off.
FOUR! Nicely cut away! Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
On middle, tucked to the leg side for a single.
On off, defended out.
Tossed up on off, Foakes plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Ben defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball on the pads, Lawrence looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Full on middle, Lawrence nudges it down to long on for a single.
Floated ball on the pads, Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball down the leg side, Foakes looks to flick but misses.
Quicker ball on off, Ben defends it out.
Full and on middle, Foakes works it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on the pads, Ben defends it out towards mid on.
Loopy ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, Foakes punches it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, worked down to mid on.
Quicker on middle, Foakes defends it onto the pitch.
Loopy ball outside off, Foakes drives it to mid off.
Flat on middle, Lawrence goes back in his crease and then plays it back to the bowler.
On the pads, nudged to the leg side.
Loopy ball on the pads, Dan works it to short mid-wicket.
EDGED AND FOUR! Just wide of first slip! Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence goes hard at that and looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and flies past first slip and into the third man fence.
On the pads, worked to mid-wicket.
Floated on the pads, Dan pads it away.
Flatter on the pads, Foakes flicks it to the deep square leg region and pick up three before the fielder cuts it off.
Floated ball on off, Lawrence defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Dan defends it out.
Shortish on off, Lawrence pushes it to cover.
Flatter ball outside off, DL punches it through the cover region for a couple.
Floated on middle, defended back to the bowler. No run.
Flighted ball on middle, Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball down the leg side, Foakes looks to flick but misses.
Well done by Rishabh Pant! Floated ball down the leg side, Ben looks to flick but misses. Pant collects and then flicks the ball back onto the stumps but Ben was in.
On the pads, Foakes pads it away.
Flatter on the pads, Foakes works it down to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Good effort in the deep! Short ball around the pads, Lawrence looks to pull but it takes the top edge. The deep square leg fielder runs ahead for the catch, dives but cannot catch it and goes into the fence behind.
Flatter ball on middle, Foakes defends it out.
On middle, nudged to the leg side.
Loopy ball on off, Foakes pushes it wide of the bowler and take a run.
Flighted ball on the pads, Lawrence flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball outside off, punched through the cover region for a couple.

NOT OUT! Missing the stumps! India lose a review! Ashwin sounded confident but pant from behind was saying that it is going down and that is what happened. Flighted ball on middle and leg, Lawrence pads it away. Ashwin appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Ashwin consults Kohli for the review and Kohli takes it. The Ball Tracker shows that it is missing the leg stump.
Flatter ball on the pads, Foakes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Shorter and on middle, Lawrence tucks it to short leg.
Floated on middle, Dan uses his feet and then pushes it down to mid on.
Leading edge but safe! Flatter ball on middle, Lawrence looks to work it to the leg side but gets a leading edge which goes to the cover region for a single.
On middle, tucked to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter on middle, Lawrence works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the stumps, Dan keeps it out.
Slower through the air and on middle, Lawrence keeps it out.
Slightly shorter, Lawrence shapes up to pull but then it turns away. He slaps it down to long on for one.
BEATEN! Foakes misreads the length there! This lands on off and then spins away. Foakes goes back to a delivery he should be forward to. Gets beaten.
On middle, Lawrence works it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air and on the pads, it is padded away.
Once again on the pads, it is kicked away by Lawrence.
On middle, this is defended.
Shorter and on middle, Lawrence makes room and pushes it through covers for one.
Tossed up on off, Foakes lunges and blocks.
On middle, Lawrence works it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Foakes works it to short leg.
Gives it nice flight and lands it on off, it is pushed to mid off.
On middle, defended.
On the stumps again, Ben defends it with his bat in front of his pad.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, Lawrence works it to square leg.
Dan comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Keeps it out.
Loopy ball on off, Lawrence blocks.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
This one is eased down to long on. Two is the call but they have to settle for one.
On middle, Foakes hangs back and keeps it out.
Flatter ball outside off, Dan cuts but finds the point fielder.
Very full ball on middle, defended to cover.
On middle, Lawrence defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball outside off, Lawrence pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence looks to punch it off the back foot but misses.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
100 up for England! Foakes plays it nicely as he comes down and works it down to long on.
A yorker on off, Lawrence jams it out towards cover for one more.
One more single! On middle, this is eased down to long on.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Outside off, Foakes pushes it through covers for one.
Plays it well! This lands on off and then there is extra bounce. Lawrence plays it with soft hands onto the ground. 5 singles from the over then.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
A little too full, this is worked back to the bowler.
On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On the pads again, this is worked to the fielder at short leg.
Loopy ball on middle, Foakes defends it onto the ground.
The arm ball, it lands on middle and then goes on with the angle. Foakes looks to defend but it goes off the outer half on the off side.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
How has that missed the off pole? What a delivery! This lands on middle and then turns square. Lawrence goes back and tries to defend but the ball goes just past the off pole.
Edgy two! Tossed up outside off, Lawrence goes after it. It goes off the outside edge past the diving second slip fielder for two.
On off, it is pushed to covers.
BEATEN! Axar is getting a lot of turn and bounce from this end! This lands on off and then turns away. Lawrence looks to block but is beaten by the away turn.
Now bowls the arm ball on middle, defended.
Flighted ball on middle, Foakes defends it to silly mid on.
Flatter ball on the pads, Foakes goes back in his crease and then pads it away.
Shorter and on middle, Ben flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Lawrence defends it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Dan uses his feet and works it to mid on.
Down the leg side, Lawrence lets it go.

OUT! That has indeed carried and it is a fine, fine catch from Rahane! Not sure why he was not confident about that! OUT flashes on the big screen and Foakes has to walk back. The gritty stand has come to an end. The change of ends for Axar has worked. He caused a lot of problems in the last over and now has got Foakes. He slows it up, lands it on off and then gets it to turn away. Foakes looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes low towards Rahane who dives to his left. He is not sure whether it has carried or not. The umpires take it upstairs. Soft signal being 'NOT OUT'. Replays roll in and they show that it has carried easily. India into the bowling all-rounders now. Trail still above 50.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this pitches and then turns. Bess looks to defend but it goes off the outer half on the off side.
Good take! OUtside off, Bess looks to sweep. This one turns away as it beats the bat. Pant does well to collect it.
Bess is off the mark! Shorter and outside off, he cuts it through point for two.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, Lawrence works it to short leg.
On the pads again, this is clipped to the man at mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, it is pushed to the man at mid off.
Quicker and on off, Lawrence goes back and defends it.
Quicker and on off, Dan stays back and blocks.
On the stumps to end the over. Lawrence pushes it to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Axar has another 5-fer! This man has made Test cricket look very easy! 4th 5-fer for him in 3 Test matches. Superb performance from the local lad. Tossed up ball outside off, Bess looks to play the slog sweep but gets an edge back to the keeper. Pant makes no mistake. India two wickets away.
BEATEN! That went straight through! Floated ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but misses.
Tossed up on middle, Leach looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated on the pads, Leach looks to flick but it hits his pads and lobs towards short leg.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
PLAY AND A MISS! Flatter ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Flatter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on and the single is taken.
BEAUTY! This lands on off and then turns away. Leach is beaten as he tries to defend.
This one goes on with the arm on the stumps. Leach blocks it.
Slower through the air, it lands outside off and then turns away. Beaten.
Goes past the outside edge again! From over the wicket now, this lands on middle and then spins away. Leach tries to block it but it whizzes past the outside edge.
On middle, defended.
On off, Lawrence pushes it to covers.
On the stumps, defended.
FOUR! Poor ball and put away! Shorter and outside off, Lawrence slaps it through covers and it races away to the fence.
FOUR! Up and over! Tossed up on off, Lawrence goes uppish, he clears mid off and it results in a boundary.
On middle, defended.
Lawrence keeps strike as he guides it towards point for one.
This lands on middle and then spins in. It hits the pad and goes over leg gully towards fine leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
Nice and solid! On middle, blocked.
Outside off, not played at.
BEATEN! This lands on off and then spins away. Leach is beaten as he tries to defend it.
Slower through the air and on middle, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
This is on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Leach comes down the track and swings, it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Lawrence takes one as he works it through mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Leach nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on the pads, Lawrence looks to flick but it brushes his pads and goes to leg slip.
On off, punched to cover.
Flatter on middle, Dan defends it out onto the pitch.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ashwin! Short ball down the leg side, Lawrence waited for it and then pulls it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Flighted ball on middle, Dan works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball on middle, tucked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Down the leg side, Lawrence lets it be.
A polite enquiry! Down the leg side, Lawrence looks to flick but misses. It hits Pant's glove and lobs towards first stlip. Nothing.
Two! Dan moves onto 49! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Another one on middle, blocked.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled! Flighted ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but gets beaten.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Ultra Edge and it is pitching outside leg. Leach survives! Flatter ball on middle and leg, it turns in. Leach looks to defend but it seems to have taken an outside edge. India appeal and the finger has gone up. Leach has taken the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows nothing while the Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching outside leg.
On off, defended to point.
BEATEN! Loopy ball outside off, Leach looks to defend but gets beaten.
Loopy ball outside off, driven to mid off.
Flighted ball outside off, played to the off side.
Flatter ball outside off, Lawrence cuts it straight to point.
FIFTY FOR DAN LAWRENCE! 2nd one for him in Tests. He has been the lone bright spot in this innings. Floated ball outside off, Lawrence punches it to cover for a single.

Almost! Gill tries hard but it pops out! Flighted ball on the pads, Leach looks to defend but it seems to have gone off the inside edge, onto the pads and goes to the short leg fielder. Gill dives but fails to hold on. The replays show that there is no bat on it.
On off, punched to cover.
Flatter ball on middle, Leach tucks it to short leg.
Floated on off, Leach pushes it to cover for a single.
BEATEN! Wow, that is some turn! Floated ball around off, it spins away. Leach looks to defend but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! Rahane has taken this one cleanly and Leach has to go! India just one wicket away from a 3-1 victory. Loopy ball on off, Leach looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to Rahane. Rahane at first slip catches it and then calmly gives the ball to the square leg umpire. The two umpires want to be sure and take it upstairs. The soft signal is out. The replays roll in and they show that Rahane has taken it cleanly. The brief resistance from Leach is over.
Flighted ball on middle, Anderson works it to the leg side for a single.
Loopy ball down the leg side, Lawrence looks to flick but misses.

OUT! TIMBER! Knocked him over and 30TH 5-five wicket haul for Ashwin! India win the match by an innings and 25 runs. Flighted ball around middle, Lawrence looks to swing it away but misses and the ball hits the timber behind. THEY TAKE THE SERIES 3-1 AND THEY QUALIFY FOR THE WTC FINAL.
